building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Desde las Tierras del Sur llegan guerreros resistentes para vender sus servicios al mejor postor.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Patrons talk as they sit around smoking from large ornamental hookahs.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los patrocinadores conversan mientras se sientan alrededor fumando de grandes narguiles ornamentales.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Larger establishments offer mouth-watering delicacies, exotic drinks and serve as social gathering places.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Establecimientos más grandes ofrecen deliciosos manjares, bebidas exóticas y sirven como lugares de encuentro social.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: An even larger establishment that offers other mouth-watering delicacies...
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Un establecimiento aún más grande que ofrece otros deliciosos manjares...

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Under a swift sunrise, the Dhows set out from the docks on their daily routine of carrying Arabyan sailors amidst the seas and oceans for various purposes, most notably pearl hunting.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Bajo un rápido amanecer, los Dhows salen de los muelles en su rutina diaria de llevar a los marineros árabes a través de mares y océanos con diversos propósitos, siendo la caza de perlas el más destacado.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Corsairs and Merchants from all walks of life can be found here, all focused on one task - to make the most coin possible, doesn't matter how it's done.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Corsarios y comerciantes de todos los ámbitos de la vida pueden encontrarse aquí, todos enfocados en una tarea: hacer la mayor cantidad de dinero posible, sin importar cómo se haga.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: In the largest Arabyan cities, you may find harbours entirely dedicated to shipping and receiving slaves. After all, it is on the backs of slaves that the greatest empires are built!
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: En las ciudades árabes más grandes, puedes encontrar puertos enteramente dedicados al envío y recepción de esclavos. ¡Después de todo, son sobre los hombros de los esclavos que se construyen los mayores imperios!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Small gardens where the aromatic coffee beans are grown.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Pequeños jardines donde se cultivan los aromáticos granos de café.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Larger plantations serve to meet the high demand for the invigorating drink.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Las plantaciones más grandes sirven para satisfacer la alta demanda de la bebida revitalizante.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The delicious aroma of freshly roasted coffee beans drifts through the streets near the roastery.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: El delicioso aroma de los granos de café recién tostados flota por las calles cerca de la tostadora.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: There are many small towns such as this dotting the large swathes of the Arabyan deserts, with its folk often minding their own business detracted from common worldly affairs.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Hay muchos pequeños pueblos como este que salpican las grandes extensiones de los desiertos árabes, con su gente a menudo ocupada en sus propios asuntos, alejados de los asuntos mundanos comunes.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: In Araby, small coastal towns such as this heavily rely on pearl trading aside from the usual fishing that goes on over here.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: En Arabia, los pequeños pueblos costeros como este dependen en gran medida del comercio de perlas, además de la pesca habitual que se realiza aquí.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Makeshift markets are a fairly common sight in Arabyan settlements. One might feel at home between hagglers trying to sway potential customers over here and the occasional thief pickpocketing a confused bystander over there.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los mercados improvisados son una vista bastante común en los asentamientos árabes. Uno podría sentirse como en casa entre los regateadores que intentan convencer a los posibles compradores aquí y el ocasional ladrón que hurta a un transeúnte confundido por allá.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Bustling ports and sea-side bazaars span the length of the coast in this town. Slowly but surely, the town is bound to grow to accustom to handling more traders from lands far and wide!
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Puertos bulliciosos y bazares junto al mar se extienden a lo largo de la costa en esta ciudad. ¡Lenta pero seguramente, la ciudad crecerá y se acostumbrará a manejar a más comerciantes de tierras lejanas!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: "Welcome friend! You will find all sorts of goods and products here! L-look, silk! Silk from faraway Cathay! Aa-and over here, this is a special product - a genie lamp! You will..."
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: "¡Bienvenido, amigo! ¡Aquí encontrarás todo tipo de bienes y productos! M-mira, ¡seda! ¡Seda de la lejana Cathay! A-aquí, esto es un producto especial: ¡una lámpara de genio! Tú verás..."

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Ships from all four corners of the world sail back and forth from these Arabyan coastal cities. Jewels of the desert abundant in resources gained by bartering with traders from the lands of faraway Cathay, mysterious realms of Nippon, jungles of Lustria, the human principalities of the Empire, and even some Norscan tribes.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los barcos de todos los rincones del mundo navegan de un lado a otro desde estas ciudades costeras árabes. ¡Joyas del desierto, abundantes en recursos, obtenidas al intercambiar con comerciantes de las lejanas tierras de Cathay, los reinos misteriosos de Nippon, las junglas de Lustria, los principados humanos del Imperio, e incluso algunas tribus norscas!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The larger Arabyan cities mark the epitome of how advanced Arabyan engineering has become. Graceful artisanship of marble-carving has produced stunning results. Dome and column, adorned with glamorous hints of gold. This is a testament of Arabyan - and why, even human - might!
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Las grandes ciudades árabes marcan el epítome de lo avanzado que se ha vuelto la ingeniería árabe. La gracia del arte de tallar mármol ha producido resultados impresionantes. Cúpulas y columnas adornadas con glamorosos toques de oro. ¡Este es un testamento del poder árabe y, por ende, humano!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Prospering betwixt marble-column and golden-dome proud, these Arabyan cities are a work of human ingenuity! Unkbeknowst to many though, you may find the usual Skaven under-city from time to time...
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Prosperando entre columnas de mármol y cúpulas doradas, estas ciudades árabes son una obra de ingenio humano. Sin embargo, muchos no lo saben, de vez en cuando se pueden encontrar las usuales ciudades subterráneas de los Skaven...

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Mighty domed palaces laced together to form structures that no living - nor dead - has ever witnessed before. These are confined within tremendously tall walls, in itself surrounded by the large city. The Sultans call this place home, and woe to any who might trespass against their will!
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Palacios enormes con cúpulas, unidos para formar estructuras que ningún ser vivo - ni muerto - ha presenciado antes. Estos están confinados dentro de enormes muros, a su vez rodeados por la gran ciudad. Los Sultanes llaman a este lugar hogar, ¡y ay de aquellos que osen traspasar su voluntad!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The Arabyans are a proud people... As such, they have built their greatest cities through sweat and blood! Unmatched in architecture and engineering, this city hosts the most grandiose bazaars and ports to be found in Araby. You might also witness the High Elven embassies and trading posts, something you would rarely find outside Ulthuan.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los árabes son un pueblo orgulloso... ¡Como tal, han construido sus grandes ciudades a base de sudor y sangre! Inigualables en arquitectura e ingeniería, esta ciudad alberga los bazares y puertos más grandiosos de Arabia. También podrías ser testigo de las embajadas y puestos comerciales de los Altos Elfos, algo que rara vez se encuentra fuera de Ulthuan.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Small camps that are called home by newly civilized Desert Tribes. They still have a long way to get accustomed to city culture, but as long as they take care of the livestock most Sultans don't really bat an eye.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Pequeños campamentos que son hogar de las recién civilizadas Tribus del Desierto. Aún tienen un largo camino por recorrer para acostumbrarse a la cultura urbana, pero mientras cuiden el ganado, la mayoría de los sultanes no les prestan mucha atención.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: In Araby, small coastal towns such as this heavily rely on pearl trading aside from the usual fishing that goes on over here.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: En Arabia, los pequeños pueblos costeros como este dependen en gran medida del comercio de perlas, además de la pesca habitual que se realiza aquí.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Villages such as these deal most of their commerce in farming and hunting. You will, however, find the occasional caravan stop somewhere that allows such villages to one day become bustling cities.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los pueblos como estos realizan la mayor parte de su comercio en agricultura y caza. Sin embargo, de vez en cuando encontrarás alguna parada de caravanas en algún lugar que permita que tales pueblos se conviertan un día en bulliciosas ciudades.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Bustling ports and sea-side bazaars span the length of the coast in this town. Slowly but surely, the town is bound to grow to accustom to handling more traders from lands far and wide!
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Puertos bulliciosos y bazares junto al mar se extienden a lo largo de la costa en esta ciudad. ¡Lenta pero seguramente, la ciudad crecerá y se acostumbrará a manejar a más comerciantes de tierras lejanas!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Whether they're on the Silk Road or not, Arabyans will always find a way to trade and make coin. And soon enough, their cities will slowly fill the old world - and perhaps the new - in marble and stone, if left unopposed!
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Ya sea que estén en la Ruta de la Seda o no, los árabes siempre encontrarán una manera de comerciar y hacer dinero. ¡Y pronto, sus ciudades llenarán lentamente el viejo mundo - y quizás el nuevo - con mármol y piedra, si no se les opone!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Ships from all four corners of the world sail back and forth from these Arabyan coastal cities. Jewels of the desert abundant in resources gained by bartering with traders from the lands of faraway Cathay, mysterious realms of Nippon, jungles of Lustria, the human principalities of the Empire, and even some Norscan tribes.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los barcos de todos los rincones del mundo navegan de un lado a otro desde estas ciudades costeras árabes. ¡Joyas del desierto, abundantes en recursos obtenidos al intercambiar con comerciantes de las lejanas tierras de Cathay, los reinos misteriosos de Nippon, las junglas de Lustria, los principados humanos del Imperio, e incluso algunas tribus norscas!

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: "100 Dinars? 200 Dinars? Do we have a deal? Remember folks, this one is well-built and young in its years! Oh-what's that? SOLD!"
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: "¿100 dinares? ¿200 dinares? ¿Tenemos un trato? Recuerden, amigos, ¡este está bien construido y es joven! ¡Ah, ¿qué es eso? ¡VENDIDO!"

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: In the Arena, a man is made and unmade a hundred times, until death.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: En la Arena, un hombre se hace y deshace cien veces, hasta la muerte.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Known as the City of Thieves, it is the largest commercial port in Araby. Home of the Great Sultan, hub of commerce and capital of Araby.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Conocida como la Ciudad de los Ladrones, es el puerto comercial más grande de Arabia. Hogar del Gran Sultán, centro de comercio y capital de Arabia.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The peaks of the Atalan Mountains are inhabited by many beasts, including the Giant Vultures and Radiant Pegasi.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Las cumbres de las Montañas Atalan están habitadas por muchas bestias, incluyendo los Buitres Gigantes y los Pegasos Radiantes.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The Arabyan College of Sorcerers teaches gifted students from across the peninsula in the ways of Magic.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: El Colegio Árabe de Hechiceros enseña a estudiantes dotados de toda la península en los caminos de la Magia.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The docks of Copher are famed for its spice trade, which earned the city the name City of Spices. But it is also feared for its pirates...
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los muelles de Copher son famosos por su comercio de especias, lo que le dio a la ciudad el nombre de Ciudad de las Especias. Pero también es temida por sus piratas...

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The memory of the night continues to haunt the Arabyans, however, there are some who crave such power. Inside these chambers sleeps the dark shadow that once devastated this land.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: El recuerdo de la noche sigue persiguiendo a los árabes, sin embargo, hay algunos que anhelan tal poder. Dentro de estas cámaras duerme la sombra oscura que una vez devastó esta tierra.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The one who was the ruler of the southern seas built this mighty fortress. Nafel Muq ruled the oceans like a tyrant, and the Arabyan corsairs continue his path.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Aquel que fue el gobernante de los mares del sur construyó esta poderosa fortaleza. Nafel Muq gobernó los océanos como un tirano, y los corsarios árabes continúan su camino.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: At last, the Maelstrom belongs to the Golden Magus and with his magic he can become the most powerful Djinn summoner in the world.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Finalmente, el Torbellino le pertenece al Mago Dorado y con su magia puede convertirse en el invocador de Djinns más poderoso del mundo.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Now the masquerade falls and the Golden Magus shows who his true loyalties lie with. The power of the Maelstrom belongs to the God of Change and he rewards his servants richly.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Ahora la máscara cae y el Mago Dorado muestra con quién están sus verdaderas lealtades. El poder del Torbellino pertenece al Dios del Cambio y recompensa generosamente a sus siervos.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The glory of the past rises here, in what was the most beautiful wonder in the world, the Gardens of Bel-Aliad. Its vision is a reflection of what Araby once was, the greatest human civilization in the world.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: La gloria del pasado se alza aquí, en lo que fue la maravilla más hermosa del mundo, los Jardines de Bel-Aliad. Su visión es un reflejo de lo que Arabia fue una vez, la mayor civilización humana en el mundo.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The sentient whirlpool at the centre of the Galleon's Graveyard pulls great sea-going vessels into its gaping maw, wherein Noctilus bides his time and awaits his chance.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: El remolino consciente en el centro del Cementerio de Galeones atrae grandes barcos hacia su enorme boca, donde Noctilus espera su oportunidad y su momento.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The legend of this terrible city has reached every corner of the globe, as it is said to be the place where all slaves taken in the mortal world eventually end up to be sold.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: La leyenda de esta terrible ciudad ha llegado a todos los rincones del mundo, ya que se dice que es el lugar donde todos los esclavos capturados en el mundo mortal finalmente terminan para ser vendidos.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Tactile and elegant, Ivory is held in the highest regard to the denizens of Ka-Sabar. This palace was built in tribute to Kasoun by the master architects of Ka-Sabar, and has become the formal residence of the ruling Sultans ever since.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Táctil y elegante, el marfil es considerado de la más alta estima por los habitantes de Ka-Sabar. Este palacio fue construido en tributo a Kasoun por los maestros arquitectos de Ka-Sabar, y ha llegado a ser la residencia formal de los sultanes gobernantes desde entonces.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: It is spoken throughout Araby that there is little about the art of sorcery that the Wizard Caliph does not know, and he specialises in the lifting and laying of curses. Of course for any service the Caliph is sure to ask a favour in return.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Se dice en toda Arabia que hay poco sobre el arte de la hechicería que el Califa Hechicero no sepa, y se especializa en levantar y poner maldiciones. Por supuesto, por cualquier servicio, el Califa seguramente pedirá un favor a cambio.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The largest of them all is the Palace of the Great Sultan. It is famous for its riches and luxuries, with large libraries brimming with ancient and unique books, and with temples decorated with idols of the Djinns, the gods of Araby.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: El más grande de todos es el Palacio del Gran Sultán. Es famoso por sus riquezas y lujos, con grandes bibliotecas llenas de libros antiguos y únicos, y templos decorados con ídolos de los Djinns, los dioses de Arabia.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: A nameless horror lives behind its border. A land that knows no other will than that of its tyrannical gods. Many have passed through it, but no one has been able to return...
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Un horror sin nombre vive tras su frontera. Una tierra que no conoce otra voluntad que la de sus dioses tiránicos. Muchos han pasado por ella, pero nadie ha podido regresar...

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: This Tower serves as a testament of Arabyan might; to those who dared pillage and burn their lands and cities for centuries. As a symbol of benevolence; from those who vowed not to do to their aggressors what was done unto them. And a mark of terror; to any who might dare threaten Araby ever again!
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Esta Torre sirve como un testamento del poder árabe; para aquellos que osaron saquear y quemar sus tierras y ciudades durante siglos. Como símbolo de benevolencia; de aquellos que juraron no hacer a sus agresores lo que les hicieron a ellos. Y una marca de terror; para cualquiera que osara amenazar a Arabia alguna vez más.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: The Aswad Scythans are loyal servants of the Tomb Kings and go to great lengths to protect and maintain their masters' crypts, in turn, the masters will not hesitate to defend their faithful subjects.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Los Escitas Aswad son leales sirvientes de los Reyes Funerarios y hacen grandes esfuerzos para proteger y mantener las criptas de sus amos; a su vez, los amos no dudarán en defender a sus fieles súbditos.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: This grandiose tomb is the greatest pride of the Arabyans. The first Great Sultan, Mullah Aklan’d, lies here. His legend still lives in the hearts of the inhabitants of this land.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Esta grandiosa tumba es el mayor orgullo de los árabes. El primer Gran Sultán, Mulá Aklan’d, yace aquí. Su leyenda aún vive en los corazones de los habitantes de esta tierra.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Inside a forgotten rocky valley near the World's Edge Mountains lies the tomb of Karitamen, the Death Scarab himself, and deadly foe to Princess Fatandira and her people. The Liche Lord is conspicuously absent, but has left behind many riches and servants, ripe for the taking...
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Dentro de un olvidado valle rocoso cerca de las Montañas del Borde del Mundo yace la tumba de Karitamen, el Escarabajo de la Muerte, y mortal enemigo de la Princesa Fatandira y su pueblo. El Señor Liche está conspicuamente ausente, pero ha dejado muchas riquezas y sirvientes, listos para ser tomados...

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: With their shadows flickering from the incandescent light of enchanted torches, the night watchmen make their rounds.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Con sus sombras parpadeando a la luz incandescente de las antorchas encantadas, los vigilantes nocturnos hacen sus rondas.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: A trained force of Watchmen scour the tunnels beneath the city, staying alert to any sign of the filthy creatures that might call these hollows home.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Una fuerza entrenada de Vigilantes recorre los túneles bajo la ciudad, manteniéndose alerta ante cualquier signo de las sucias criaturas que puedan llamar a estos huecos su hogar.

building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_original: Hunters, trackers and warriors of the highest calibre all do their part to patrol the underground in search of foul ratkin.
building_short_description_texts_short_d.value_translated: Cazadores, rastreadores y guerreros de la más alta calidad cumplen su parte para patrullar el subsuelo en busca de los repugnantes Hombre Rata.

campaign_group_rituals_unlock_text_ovn_a.value_original: [[col:dark_r]]This rite will unlock after reaching rank 7 with any character.[[/col]]
campaign_group_rituals_unlock_text_ovn_a.value_translated: [[col:dark_r]]Este rito se desbloqueará después de alcanzar el rango 7 con cualquier personaje.[[/col]]

campaign_localised_strings_string_rhox_a.value_original: [[col:red]]This unit will become available when your allegiance towards Araby reaches 100%[[/col]]
campaign_localised_strings_string_rhox_a.value_translated: [[col:red]]Esta unidad estará disponible cuando tu lealtad hacia Araby alcance el 100%[[/col]]

campaign_localised_strings_string_rhox_a.value_original: [[col:red]]One of the Royal Djinn will unlock for every milestone you make for Jaffar's Revenge[[/col]]
campaign_localised_strings_string_rhox_a.value_translated: [[col:red]]Se desbloqueará uno de los Djinn Reales por cada hito alcanzado en la Venganza de Jaffar[[/col]]

campaign_localised_strings_string_rhox_a.value_original: [[col:red]]One of the Royal Djinn will unlock for every two attained Piece of Eight[[/col]]
campaign_localised_strings_string_rhox_a.value_translated: [[col:red]]Se desbloqueará uno de los Djinn Reales por cada dos Piezas de Ocho obtenidas[[/col]]

campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_original: [[col:yellow]]There is a 50% chance that a battle will take place[[/col]]
campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_translated: [[col:yellow]]Hay un 50% de probabilidad de que se produzca una batalla[[/col]]
[[col:yellow]]Lucha y obtén el mapa del tesoro[[/col]]

campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_original: You gained access to the Royal Djinns!
campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_translated: ¡Has conseguido acceso a los Djinn Reales!

campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_original: You gained access to the Tomb Kings mightiest units!
campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_translated: ¡Has conseguido acceso a las unidades más poderosas de los Reyes Funerarios!

campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_original: One of the Royal Djinn is under your control!
campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_translated: ¡Uno de los Djinn Reales está bajo tu control!

campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_original: Mehmed the Butcher has joined you.
campaign_payload_ui_details_description_.value_translated: Mehmed el Carnicero se ha unido a ti.

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: Allow these warriors to return to their homelands, for a ransom. Despite dipping into their treasury, the enemy will appreciate such a deed.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: Permite a estos guerreros regresar a sus tierras a cambio de un rescate. A pesar de afectar sus arcas, el enemigo apreciará tal acción.

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: Herd these wretches into our slave camps and harems! They shall toil for us!
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: ¡Reúne a estos desgraciados en nuestros campos de esclavos y harenes! ¡Trabajarán para nosotros!

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: Allow these warriors to return to their homelands, for a ransom. Despite dipping into their treasury, the enemy will appreciate such a deed.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: Permite a estos guerreros regresar a sus tierras a cambio de un rescate. A pesar de afectar sus arcas, el enemigo apreciará tal acción.

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: Leave no captives alive. The foe and their allies will not look upon you kindly, but their enemies will respect your decision.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: No dejes cautivos con vida. El enemigo y sus aliados no te verán con buenos ojos, pero sus enemigos respetarán tu decisión.

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: Defeated warriors can be persuaded to follow a victorious Lord.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: Los guerreros derrotados pueden ser persuadidos de seguir a un Señor victorioso.

campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_original: The Arabyan slave markets can accommodate an immeasurable number of defeated and lost souls.
campaign_post_battle_captive_options_des.value_translated: Los mercados de esclavos árabes pueden acomodar una cantidad inmensurable de almas derrotadas y perdidas.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Punish the rival caravan for their insolence
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Castigar a la caravana rival por su insolencia

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Retreat and bind them from afar!
Demand the return of the weapons
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Exigir la devolución de las armas
No vale la pena el problema

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Rob the Scrapper and claim his scrap for yourself
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Robar al Chatarrero y quedarte con su chatarra
Mantener a raya a estas bestias
Aceptar la ayuda de los ogros
Usar el regalo para reclutar mercenarios

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Let them get whoever is next
These fools dare have better steeds than us?! We must attack these upstarts and take their Flying Carpets for ourselves!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¡Estos tontos se atreven a tener mejores monturas que nosotros! ¡Debemos atacar a esos advenedizos y quedarnos con sus Alfombras Voladoras!

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Any caravan master wealthy enough to afford such luxury will know the value of our cargo. We'll use it to buy ALL his carpets, rather than simply scavenging whatever's left after a battle.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Cualquier líder de caravana lo bastante rico para costear semejante lujo sabrá valorar nuestro cargamento. Lo usaremos para comprar TODAS sus alfombras, en lugar de limitarnos a saquear lo que quede tras el combate.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We ready ourselves for a battle, but it's over too quickly. The ropes are blurs of carnage, and a whole unit is slaughtered before we flee the outpost! At least the men who survive are hardened by the experience.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Nos preparamos para la batalla, pero termina demasiado rápido. Las cuerdas son borrones de carnicería y una unidad entera es masacrada antes de que huyamos del puesto avanzado. ¡Al menos los supervivientes salen fortalecidos por la experiencia!

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We retreat before the Rope Djinns attack, and our Magicians begin the rituals of binding. This will take some time...
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Nos retiramos antes de que las Cuerdas Djinn ataquen, y nuestros Magos inician los rituales de atadura. Esto llevará algo de tiempo...

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Demand the return of the weapons
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Exigir la devolución de las armas

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: And inform them where they can acquire more
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: E informarle dónde puede conseguir más

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: This Noble is not their Ancestor.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Ese Noble no es su Antepasado.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: One lousy Caravan isn't worth the bother. The Cathayans can keep their lives for today, and their paltry cargo.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Una mísera Caravana no vale la molestia. Los cathayanos pueden conservar sus vidas por hoy, y su ínfima carga.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: "We're sorry but at the moment we're a bit short on slaves"
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Lo sentimos, pero por el momento andamos escasos de esclavos.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: "They drive a hard bargain, but we really don't want to anger them "
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Exigen un precio alto, pero preferimos no enfadarlos.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: “Whatever they are digging for might fetch a nice price at the marketplace…”
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Sea lo que sea que estén cavando, podría venderse muy bien en el mercado…”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: "They barter well for torturers. We accept."
We were short on short slaves
“The extra hand is nice but the gold is nicer.”
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Un apoyo extra está bien, pero el oro es mejor.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: “Join us. We can always use an extra short hand.”
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Únete a nosotros. Un par de manos bajas siempre vienen bien.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Fight them! Break their ancient bones and seize their wealth.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¡Luchen contra ellos! Romped sus viejos huesos y tomad sus riquezas.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We must not be distracted from our goal. Leave them to their Unlife.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: No debemos distraernos de nuestro objetivo. Déjenlos con su No Vida.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: “Leave the wagons and take all you can carry.”
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Dejen los carros y llévense todo lo que puedan.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Join us. It's not a choice
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Únanse a nosotros. No es una elección

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Empower the existing army with the corpses
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Fortalecer el ejército existente con los cadáveres

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: “I think I’ll just take your scrap.”
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Creo que me quedaré con tu chatarra.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: “How about we show them who really owns this land?.”
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “¿Qué tal si les mostramos quién es el auténtico dueño de estas tierras?”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: “Though it never feels good to validate a haughty elfs, help is always needed… ”
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Aunque no es agradable satisfacer la altivez de un elfo, siempre se necesita ayuda…”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Hungry are they? Well in that case they can fill their bellies with our blades!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¿Tienen hambre? Entonces que llenen sus estómagos con nuestras espadas.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: What's a few sacrifices for the many? It was probably time to cull the weak anyway – these Daemons are doing you a favour!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¿Qué importan unos sacrificios por el bien de muchos? Probablemente era hora de purgar a los débiles de todos modos; ¡estos Demonios te hacen un favor!

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We will crush this host and make our consignment even more lucrative than it already is!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¡Aplastaremos a este ejército y haremos nuestro cargamento aún más lucrativo de lo que ya es!

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Hostilities and losses can be easily avoided if we just keep moving.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Es fácil evitar hostilidades y pérdidas si seguimos avanzando.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: To end a fight as quickly and easily as possible, one needs the capacity to deal the lethal blow.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Para terminar un combate rápida y fácilmente, se necesita la capacidad de asestar un golpe letal.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: One who can endure the most dangerous and prolonged attacks has the best chance of landing a lethal counterattack.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Quien pueda resistir los ataques más peligrosos y prolongados tiene la mejor oportunidad de asestar un contraataque letal.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Who are we to leave these poor Ogre mercenaries without work? Times are hard, after all!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¿Quiénes somos para dejar sin trabajo a estos pobres mercenarios ogros? Los tiempos son duros, después de todo.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: You are a strong and independent. Who needs an Ogre anyway!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Eres fuerte e independiente. ¿Quién necesita un ogro de todos modos?

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: The urge to sacrifice one of the retinue into this strange formation is hard to ignore; it feels like there is great power to be had here.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: La tentación de sacrificar a alguien del séquito en esta extraña formación es difícil de ignorar; parece haber un gran poder aquí.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Ignore it – it is best not to meddle in things we do not understand.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Ignóralo: es mejor no entrometernos en cosas que no comprendemos.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We can handle a few off-road chicanes – any potential losses will probably cost us less in the long run than gaining a reputation for tardiness.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Podemos sortear algunas chicanas fuera de la carretera: las posibles pérdidas a largo plazo costarán menos que obtener fama de impuntuales.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We should stick to the main route and avoid exposing the cargo to any unnecessary risks.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Debemos ceñirnos a la ruta principal y evitar exponer la carga a riesgos innecesarios.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Kill some rats and reduce the length of our journey? Sounds like a win-win!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¿Matar algunas ratas y acortar la duración de nuestro viaje? Parece un ganar-ganar.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We don't know how many rats are in this convoy. The last thing we need is to be overwhelmed by the vermin!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: No sabemos cuántas ratas hay en este convoy. Lo último que necesitamos es vernos sobrepasados por la plaga.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: The smell of gunpowder is preferable to the smell of rotting flesh. Eliminate them!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: El olor a pólvora es preferible al hedor de la carne podrida. Elimínalos.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Their sacrifice allows us to continue without further losses.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Su sacrificio nos permite seguir sin más pérdidas.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: "We do not know who these strange people are, but their offer is kind."
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “No sabemos quiénes son estas gentes extrañas, pero su oferta es amable.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: “How would you like to work for me?”
Their attempts at an ambush are frankly so embarrassing it would be an insult to the Great Djinn to let them live.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Sus intentos de emboscada son tan patéticos que sería un insulto al Gran Djinn dejarlos con vida.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: They might get lucky one day. Probably not any time soon, though.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Quizá algún día tengan suerte… aunque no parece que vaya a ser pronto.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We don't need any guidance! We have an excellent sense of direction, thank you very much!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¡No necesitamos guía alguna! Tenemos un excelente sentido de la orientación, ¡gracias!

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We need to reach our destination quickly; this guide had better be worth the price!
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Debemos llegar rápido a nuestro destino; esperemos que valga la pena lo que cobra.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: "May the Djinns never guide us along that path again."
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: “Que los Djinn no vuelvan a guiarnos por ese camino.”

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: With this beast in our Caravan’s ranks, assailants will not consider us an easy target.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Con esta bestia en las filas de la Caravana, los atacantes no nos considerarán un blanco fácil.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: It would be foolish to part with some of our cargo – we have no need for this beast and can adequately protect ourselves.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Sería insensato desprendernos de parte de nuestra carga; no necesitamos esta bestia y podemos protegernos adecuadamente.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We can brook no frailty in this Caravan. This is time well invested.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: No podemos tolerar debilidad alguna en esta Caravana. Es tiempo bien invertido.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Training is always important, but we must not lose track of time.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: El entrenamiento siempre es importante, pero no debemos perder de vista el tiempo.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: We cannot risk this untested path.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: No podemos arriesgarnos con este camino sin probar.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Our troops can handle a few loss of lives.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Nuestras tropas pueden manejar la pérdida de unas cuantas vidas.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: Rub the Tree are you daft? There shall be no lamp unrubbed on my path.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: ¿Frotar el Árbol estás loco? No dejaré lámpara sin frotar en mi camino.

cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_original: This is obviously a test. And I am a generous man.
cdir_events_dilemma_choice_details_local.value_translated: Obviamente es una prueba. Y soy un hombre generoso.

character_skills_localised_description_B.value_original: Ibn Naggazar was a brilliant, if somewhat maniacal Arabyan sorcerer. Whilst it is unknown whether his madness sprang from isolation, too many attempts at creating intoxicating elixirs or the honeyed promises of whispering daemons. There can be no doubt he was utterly mad.
character_skills_localised_description_B.value_translated: Ibn Naggazar fue un brillante, aunque algo maniático, hechicero árabe. Aunque se desconoce si su locura surgió del aislamiento, de demasiados intentos por crear elixires embriagadores o de las dulces promesas de demonios susurrantes, no cabe duda de que estaba completamente loco.

character_skills_localised_description_D.value_original: Let us turn the oasis into wine so that the crusaders may succumb to their beloved tipple.
character_skills_localised_description_D.value_translated: Convirtamos el oasis en vino para que los cruzados sucumban a su amada bebida.

character_skills_localised_description_M.value_original: Hailing from the highest peaks of the World's Edge Mountains, Arabyans just like the northern Imperials are willing to pay vast sums of gold for a single egg or chick such the renown of these majestic beasts.
character_skills_localised_description_M.value_translated: Provenientes de las cumbres más altas de las Montañas del Borde del Mundo, los árabes, al igual que los Imperiales del norte, están dispuestos a pagar grandes sumas de oro por un solo huevo o polluelo, dada la fama de estas majestuosas bestias.

character_skills_localised_description_S.value_original: Living in such a hostile land gives warriors and beasts alike a great advantage.
character_skills_localised_description_S.value_translated: Vivir en una tierra tan hostil otorga una gran ventaja tanto a los guerreros como a las bestias.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: As captain of Jaffar's Black Scimitar Guard, he never leaves his side for an instant, neither night or day.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Como capitán de la Guardia de Cimitarra Negra de Jaffar, nunca se separa de su lado ni un instante, ni de noche ni de día.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Wherever his master goes, Wazar will follow.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Dondequiera que su maestro vaya, Wazar lo seguirá.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: As a trusted retainer of Jaffar, Wazar speaks with his authority when he is sent out to lead the troops.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Como fiel criado de Jaffar, Wazar habla con su autoridad cuando se le envía para liderar las tropas.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: In a world full of dangers far greater than humans, a good guardian must be able to cope with anything.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: En un mundo lleno de peligros mucho mayores que los humanos, un buen guardián debe ser capaz de hacer frente a cualquier cosa.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Loyalty is rewarded but unfaithfulness is severely punished.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: La lealtad es recompensada, pero la infidelidad es severamente castigada.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Only the very best is good enough for Jaffar's personal retinue.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Solo lo mejor de lo mejor es suficiente para la guardia personal de Jaffar.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Wazar is an insurmountable fighter. He would be unstoppable even if the sky crashed down on him.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Wazar es un luchador insuperable. Sería imparable incluso si el cielo cayera sobre él.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Back in the Borderlands, Fatandira had quite the reputation as a markswoman among her troops. Since returning to her people, she has applied her skills to the Scythan way of the hunter.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: En las Tierras Fronterizas, Fatandira tenía una gran reputación como tiradora entre sus tropas. Desde su regreso a su pueblo, ha aplicado sus habilidades al modo de caza escita.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: "Be as cunning as the sand fox, strike as swift as the falcon!"
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: "¡Sé tan astuta como el zorro de arena, ataca tan rápido como el halcón!"

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Taken by Fatandira from the tomb of the Liche Lord Karitamen in the Borderlands, this pair of Nehekharan Khopeshes magically enhance their owner's combat skills, and weakens anyone struck by them.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Tomadas por Fatandira de la tumba del Señor Liche Karitamen en las Tierras Fronterizas, este par de Khopeshes Nehekharanos mejoran mágicamente las habilidades de combate de su portador y debilitan a cualquiera golpeado por ellos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Given to Fatandira as a gift by the Scythans, Saqir is a mighty specimen of Desert Roc, giant and intelligent birds of prey that fly high above the deserts of Araby. The animal quickly bonded with her, and now they soar the battlefield together.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Entregado a Fatandira como regalo por los Escitas, Saqir es un poderoso ejemplar de Roc del Desierto, gigantescas e inteligentes aves de presa que vuelan alto sobre los desiertos de Arabia. El animal rápidamente creó un vínculo con ella, y ahora sobrevuelan el campo de batalla juntos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: This ancient magical lamellar cuirass is said to have belonged to a legendary warrior queen of the Scythans who killed one of the great Priest Kings of Ancient Nehekhara in battle. The Scythans, believing Fatandira to be a reincarnation of that queen, have granted to her this ancient artifact.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Esta antigua coraza lamelar mágica se dice que perteneció a una legendaria reina guerrera de los Escitas que mató a uno de los grandes Reyes Sacerdotes de la Antigua Nehekhara en batalla. Los Escitas, creyendo que Fatandira es una reencarnación de esa reina, le han otorgado este antiguo artefacto.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Born to a family of Arabyan caravan nomads, Fatandira is as comfortable on the saddle as on foot.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Nacida en una familia de nómadas de caravanas árabes, Fatandira se siente tan cómoda en la silla como a pie.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Fatandira had always known that she was descended from Arabyan nomads, but it was only recently, on her journey to the Southlands, that she discovered her Scythan legacy. Now she is the undisputed leader of her ancestral tribe.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Fatandira siempre supo que descendía de nómadas árabes, pero solo recientemente, en su viaje a las Tierras del Sur, descubrió su legado escita. Ahora es la líder indiscutible de su tribu ancestral.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Since her tenure as Princess in the Borderlands, Fatandira has sought to end the bigotry and hate that plague any land she rules. Her principality might be long gone, but the ideal stands strong.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Desde su tiempo como Princesa en las Tierras Fronterizas, Fatandira ha buscado terminar con el prejuicio y el odio que azotan cualquier tierra que gobierna. Su principado puede haber desaparecido, pero el ideal sigue firme.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Even back in the Border Princes, Fatandira was well known for her cavalry tactics and the swiftness of her mounted troops. Imagine what she can do with a saddle-born people such as the Scythans under her command.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Incluso en las Tierras Fronterizas, Fatandira era bien conocida por sus tácticas de caballería y la rapidez de sus tropas montadas. Imagina lo que puede hacer con un pueblo nacido para la silla como los Escitas bajo su mando.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Since her arrival at Scythan lands, Fatandira has been hailed as "Al-Kahina", The Prophetess, by her people. The Scythans claim that she's the hero of legend that will banish the Darkness with the Golden God by her side. Fatandira herself doesn't quite believe the legend, but keeps up the appearance for the morale of her troops and well-being of her people.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Desde su llegada a las tierras escitas, Fatandira ha sido aclamada como "Al-Kahina", La Profetisa, por su pueblo. Los Escitas afirman que ella es la heroína de la leyenda que desterrará la Oscuridad con el Dios Dorado a su lado. Fatandira misma no cree del todo en la leyenda, pero mantiene la apariencia por la moral de sus tropas y el bienestar de su pueblo.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: "...From now on my destiny will be to lift these people out of ignorance and poverty, to prevent them from becoming as paranoid and vicious as the villagers who butchered my family. This I swear."
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: "...A partir de ahora, mi destino será sacar a esta gente de la ignorancia y la pobreza, evitar que se conviertan en tan paranoicos y viciosos como los aldeanos que masacraron a mi familia. Esto lo juro."

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Fatandira is a woman with an iron determination. She leads honestly, and personally ensures that her troops have talent in battle and good sense out of it.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Fatandira es una mujer con una determinación de hierro. Ella lidera con honestidad, y se asegura personalmente de que sus tropas tengan talento en la batalla y buen juicio fuera de ella.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Fatandira has adapted her famously stealthy cavalry strikes from the rough terrain of the Border Princes to the sands of Araby and Nehekhara almost seamlessly.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Fatandira ha adaptado sus famosas y sigilosas emboscadas de caballería desde el terreno accidentado de los Príncipes Fronterizos hasta las arenas de Arabia y Nehekhara casi sin esfuerzo.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The secret of the Golden Magus' sorcerous might resides in his connection, or "aethyric tether" with 3 magic urns in his possession. Imprisoned inside are 3 powerful elemental spirits, siphoned of their power for the Magus' benefit.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Del mar tomamos, al mar damos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Magus' ostentatious golden robes are not just a flamboyant show of wealth, they possess potent enchantments that the Magus discovered in a parchment at the ruined city of Bel-Aliad. Besides providing protection from harm, these wards are curiously nocive to the Undead.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Las ostentosas túnicas doradas del Mago no son solo una muestra extravagante de riqueza, poseen poderosos encantamientos que el Mago descubrió en un pergamino en la ciudad arruinada de Bel-Aliad. Además de proporcionar protección contra el daño, estos conjuros son curiosamente nocivos para los No Muertos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Though vigorous for his old age, the Golden Magus often rides to battle on one of his many camels - out of flamboyance if anything else.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Aunque vigoroso para su avanzada edad, el Mago Dorado a menudo cabalga a la batalla en uno de sus muchos camellos, más por extravagancia que por otra cosa.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Much like the Magus' infamous flagship, this enchanted skiff is proof of his mastery over the Djinn. This is one of the Golden Magus' favourite ways to ride to battle.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Al igual que el infame buque insignia del Mago, este esquife encantado es prueba de su dominio sobre los Djinn. Esta es una de las formas favoritas del Mago Dorado para cabalgar hacia la batalla.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: One of the Golden Magus' most infamous creations, this fiery curved sword is kept most of the time inside a jar filled with a slimy orange solution. When drawn out of it, the sword catches a mystical fire that the Magus' uses for battle, theatrics and summoning Djinn spirits. Contrary to popular belief, the ship is named after the sword.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Una de las creaciones más infames del Mago Dorado, esta espada curva y ardiente se guarda la mayor parte del tiempo dentro de un frasco lleno de una solución anaranjada y viscosa. Cuando se extrae, la espada captura un fuego místico que el Mago utiliza para la batalla, el espectáculo y la invocación de espíritus Djinn. Contrariamente a la creencia popular, el barco lleva el nombre de la espada.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Beneath all the eccentricity and gaudiness hides a callous corsair, eager to bring more magical treasures to his collection, more slaves to his servitude, more concubines to his harem and more power to himself.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Al igual que el infame buque insignia del Mago, este esquife encantado es prueba de su dominio sobre los Djinn. Esta es una de las formas favoritas del Mago Dorado para cabalgar hacia la batalla.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Golden Magus is an expert in the art of binding the elemental spirits known as "Djinns" to his will. Stored in the Magus' flagship are thousands of warded urns, each containing a potent Djinn ready and willing to obey his every command.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: El Mago Dorado es un experto en el arte de atar los espíritus elementales conocidos como "Djinns" a su voluntad. Almacenadas en el buque insignia del Mago hay miles de urnas protegidas, cada una conteniendo un potente Djinn listo y dispuesto a obedecer todas sus órdenes.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Golden Magus can impart much knowledge onto those aspirants willing to learn the sorcerous arts - if they can stand the eccentric nature of his lessons and the Magus' ever so condescending manners.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: El Mago Dorado puede impartir mucho conocimiento a aquellos aspirantes dispuestos a aprender las artes hechiceras, si pueden soportar la naturaleza excéntrica de sus lecciones y los modales tan condescendientes del Mago.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Golden Magus personally hand selects the ogres that will serve under him. This ensures that only the most brutish and blood-thirsty of their ilk fill his ranks.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: El Mago Dorado selecciona personalmente a los ogros que le servirán. Esto asegura que solo los más brutales y sedientos de sangre de su especie llenen sus filas.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: For someone who cultivates the image of an elderly eccentric scholar, the Golden Magus is surprisingly spry, fast and adept at combat.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Para alguien que cultiva la imagen de un excéntrico y anciano erudito, el Mago Dorado es sorprendentemente ágil, rápido y hábil en combate.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: From the sea we take, to the sea we give.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Del mar tomamos, al mar damos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Some whisper that the Magus is in complete thrall of the malignant Architect of Fate. Nonsense, of course, but like with all good rumours, there's might be a grain of truth to it...
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Algunos susurran que el Mago está completamente bajo el hechizo del maligno Arquitecto del Destino. Una tontería, por supuesto, pero como con todos los buenos rumores, puede que haya algo de verdad en ello...

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Golden Magus' mastery over the elements of air, fire and water is exceptional, especially for a human. His powers come from his most prized possessions, 3 Royal Djinns from who he draws his magical might from.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: El dominio del Mago Dorado sobre los elementos de aire, fuego y agua es excepcional, especialmente para un humano. Sus poderes provienen de sus más preciadas posesiones, 3 Djinns Reales de los que extrae su poder mágico.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Without a doubt, the Sultan of the Seas is a powerful sorcerer. Besides Djinn, however, he can also bind darker beings. This power is granted to him by his supposedly true master, the Chaos God Tzeentch.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Sin lugar a dudas, el Sultán de los Mares es un poderoso hechicero. Además de los Djinns, también puede atar a seres más oscuros. Este poder le es otorgado por su supuesto verdadero amo, el Dios del Caos Tzeentch.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Magus has enslaved many a Djinn to his will, to such degree that they cannot reject any of his wishes and commands. Djinns though are capricious and free-spirited entities, and their service should not be taken for granted.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: El Mago ha esclavizado a muchos Djinns a su voluntad, de tal forma que no pueden rechazar ninguno de sus deseos y órdenes. Sin embargo, los Djinns son entidades caprichosas y de espíritu libre, y su servicio no debe ser tomado a la ligera.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Jaffar is a vainglorious man, it is no wonder then that the prestigious camel is one of his favourite mounts to ride into battle.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Jaffar es un hombre vanidoso, no es de extrañar entonces que el prestigioso camello sea una de sus monturas favoritas para cabalgar en la batalla.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: From on top the howdah of a mighty Arabyan Royal Elephant, Sultan Jaffar gazes down upon the battlefield with only imperious cruelty and disdain in his eyes.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Desde lo alto del howdah de un imponente Elefante Real Árabe, el Sultán Jaffar observa el campo de batalla con solo crueldad y desdén en sus ojos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Jaffar's hunger for power knows no bounds. There's no pact he won't make or enemy he won't crush on his path to conquest.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: El hambre de poder de Jaffar no tiene límites. No hay pacto que no haga ni enemigo que no aplaste en su camino hacia la conquista.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Jaffar condemns all who oppose him to a life of slavery. Arabyans, Estalians, Bretonnians, Greenskins, no matter who or what they are, all enemies of Jaffar are to kneel before the Great Sultan and serve him.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Jaffar condena a todos los que se le oponen a una vida de esclavitud. Árabes, Estalianos, Bretonianos, Pielesverdes, no importa quién o qué sean, todos los enemigos de Jaffar deben arrodillarse ante el Gran Sultán y servirle.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Black Scimitar Guard is Sultan Jaffar's personal elite bodyguard. They are devoted to their Sultan and aligned with Jaffar's goals of Arabyan dominance.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: La Guardia de Cimitarra Negra es el cuerpo de élite personal del Sultán Jaffar. Están dedicados a su Sultán y alineados con los objetivos de Jaffar de la dominación árabe.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Jaffar possesses a compelling charisma with which he has been able to sway many Arabyan tribes and city-states to his side.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Jaffar posee un carisma cautivador con el que ha logrado inclinar a muchas tribus árabes y ciudades-estado hacia su lado.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: "Nothing will stop me, not the Northerners, the Elves, the Dwarfs, Settra's lackeys or anyone else! I will rule this world, or see it burnt to ashes around me!"
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: "¡Nada me detendrá, ni los del Norte, ni los Elfos, ni los Enanos, ni los lacayos de Settra, ni nadie más! ¡Gobernaré este mundo, o lo veré arder en cenizas a mi alrededor!"

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: "No land shall remain beyond my grasp. No kingdom shall be beyond my mandate. Go forth. Conquer. Rule."
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: "Ninguna tierra quedará fuera de mi alcance. Ningún reino quedará fuera de mi mandato. Adelante. Conquistar. Gobernar."

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Those proved in battle may take a sacred vow to their god Tutankhanut and serve as his mortal champion.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Aquellos que han probado su valía en batalla pueden tomar un voto sagrado hacia su dios Tutankhanut y servir como su campeón mortal.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Sheikhs ensure that there are always enough recruits available for the Sultan's armies.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Los Sheikhs se aseguran de que siempre haya suficientes reclutas disponibles para los ejércitos del Sultán.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Sheikhs of the cities are proud of their troops and especially of their cavalry so that no expense is spared either on their equipment or maintenance
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Los Sheikhs de las ciudades están orgullosos de sus tropas y especialmente de su caballería, por lo que no escatiman en gastos ni en su equipo ni en su mantenimiento.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: One of Jaffar's most efficient and brutal generals, he's rightly feared by the enemies of the Sultan.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Uno de los generales más eficientes y brutales de Jaffar, es justamente temido por los enemigos del Sultán.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Elephants are unstoppable beasts. Trained on the battlefield, they lead Araby's leaders to war, wiping out everything that gets in their way.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Los elefantes son bestias imparables. Entrenados en el campo de batalla, llevan a los líderes de Arabia a la guerra, arrasando con todo lo que se interpone en su camino.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The finest horses in Araby, bred for their endurance and fiery temperament, barded for further protection.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Los mejores caballos de Arabia, criados por su resistencia y su temperamento fogoso, equipados con bardas para una mayor protección.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: These noble beasts absorb the sun's heat, transmuting it into the burning light that flows over their skin like ripples of brightest flame.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Estas nobles bestias absorben el calor del sol, transformándolo en la luz ardiente que fluye sobre su piel como ondas de la llama más brillante.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The Sultan demands conquest and we will give him nothing else.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: El Sultán exige conquista y no le daremos nada más.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Mehmed favors using his light cavalry to weaken the enemy and then smashes them with his cataphracts.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Mehmed favorece usar su caballería ligera para debilitar al enemigo y luego aplastarlos con sus catafractos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The sun-blackened Dervishers march under the Black Lizard.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Los Derviches ennegrecidos por el sol marchan bajo el Lagarto Negro.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Not only is his brutality frightening, but also his deadly skill in close combat.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: No solo su brutalidad es aterradora, sino también su mortal destreza en combate cuerpo a cuerpo.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: These lands now belong to the Great Sultan. Put those worms to good use and see to it that his empire prospers!
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Estas tierras ahora pertenecen al Gran Sultán. ¡Pon a esos gusanos a trabajar y asegúrate de que su imperio prospere!

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Mehmed earned his sobriquet after the Battle of Nine Jackals, in which he slaughtered a force of Bretonnian crusaders. He left only one man alive to bear the tale to his countrymen, but only after he had chopped off his hands.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Mehmed ganó su apodo después de la Batalla de los Nueve Chacal, en la cual masacró a una fuerza de cruzados bretonianos. Dejó a un solo hombre con vida para que llevara la historia a sus compatriotas, pero solo después de haberle cortado las manos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The fierce Sheikhs of the desert are local leaders, being renowned warriors and military men.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Los feroces Sheikhs del desierto son líderes locales, conocidos como guerreros y hombres militares.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Despite the slander that envious men like to spread, most Grand Viziers in Araby are loyal servants to their lieges and dedicated administrators of their assigned provinces.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: A pesar de la difamación que los hombres envidiosos suelen esparcir, la mayoría de los Grandes Vizires de Arabia son leales sirvientes de sus señores y dedicados administradores de sus provincias asignadas.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The mount of any self-respecting Arabyan gentleman.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: La montura de cualquier caballero árabe que se respete a sí mismo.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: From atop this wondrous carriage, the Vizier calls upon the elemental spirits to aid his armies.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Desde lo alto de esta maravillosa carroza, el Vizir invoca a los espíritus elementales para que ayuden a sus ejércitos.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: A Djinn bound to a piece of furniture to make it fly.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Un Djinn atado a una alfombra para hacerla volar.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The mount of any self-respecting Arabyan gentleman.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: La montura de cualquier caballero árabe que se respete a sí mismo.
