character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Un Djinn atado a una alfombra para hacerla volar.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: The rumours about the dubious moral integrity of Arabyan Grand Viziers are not entirely unfounded, for there are many among them who abuse their privileges to indulge in the study of the Dark Arts.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Los rumores sobre la dudosa integridad moral de los Grandes Vizires árabes no son del todo infundados, pues hay muchos entre ellos que abusan de sus privilegios para entregarse al estudio de las Artes Oscuras.

character_skills_localised_description_a.value_original: Many Grand Viziers reach their lofty positions thanks to both their knowledge in the magical arts and their advances in the sciences, for in Araby there's little difference between the study of the natural world and the supernatural world.
character_skills_localised_description_a.value_translated: Muchos Grandes Vizires alcanzan sus elevados cargos gracias tanto a su conocimiento en las artes mágicas como a sus avances en las ciencias, pues en Arabia hay poca diferencia entre el estudio del mundo natural y el sobrenatural.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: From a far-flung tribe, their power and wealth is a great asset.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: De una tribu lejana, su poder y riqueza son un gran activo.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: They will do anything in their pursuit of power even bargaining with Chaos or scheming with Ratmen.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Harán lo que sea necesario en su búsqueda de poder, incluso pactando con el Caos o conspirando con los Hombres Rata.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A sorcerer of skill can bend Djinn to their will, the spirit fighting with every ounce of its strength against its master's enemies, making the magical jars they come from highly sought after.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Un hechicero hábil puede doblegar a los Djinn a su voluntad, el espíritu luchando con todas sus fuerzas contra los enemigos de su maestro, lo que hace que las jarras mágicas de donde provienen sean muy codiciadas.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The enemy of my enemy is my friend. Even if that friend is heavily mutated.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El enemigo de mi enemigo es mi amigo. Incluso si ese amigo está fuertemente mutado.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Elephants are unstoppable beasts. Trained on the battlefield, they lead Araby's leaders to war, wiping out everything that gets in their way.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Los elefantes son bestias imparables. Entrenados en el campo de batalla, llevan a los líderes de Arabia a la guerra, arrasando con todo lo que se interpone en su camino.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: They try to protect the innocent and drive evil from the lands and while the northern men can't see past their own prejudices but there are others in this world who fight for good.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Tratan de proteger a los inocentes y alejar el mal de las tierras, y aunque los hombres del norte no pueden ver más allá de sus propios prejuicios, hay otros en este mundo que luchan por el bien.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Inside this ornate staff decorated with snake motifs is bound a malignant and ancient Serpent Djinn, imprisoned by powerful enchantments woven by Jaffar. Only Jaffar's will is strong enough to temporarily unleash it upon his enemies on the battlefield.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Dentro de este bastón ornamentado decorado con motivos de serpientes está atado un maligno y antiguo Djinn Serpiente, encarcelado por poderosos encantamientos tejidos por Jaffar. Solo la voluntad de Jaffar es lo suficientemente fuerte como para liberarlo temporalmente contra sus enemigos en el campo de batalla.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Ancient sword art which dazzles the many who have not seen it.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Antigua técnica de espada que deslumbra a muchos que no la han visto.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Just in case...
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Por si acaso...

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: They twist and turn like a fierce sandstorm.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Se retuercen y giran como una feroz tormenta de arena.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: It is said that Armour fashioned from the carapace of the Dune Scorpion is stronger and lighter than any metal variety.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Se dice que la armadura hecha del caparazón del Escorpión de las Dunas es más fuerte y más ligera que cualquier variedad metálica.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A great man, master of war, risen through the ranks and rewarded with the Crescent Seal giving them the authority to lead a great Arabyan War Throng.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Un gran hombre, maestro de la guerra, ascendido por méritos y premiado con el Sello Creciente, dándole la autoridad para liderar una gran Horda de Guerra Árabe.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Some say he was born on a Dhow but all agree he's a master of the sea.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Algunos dicen que nació en un Dhow, pero todos coinciden en que es un maestro del mar.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Not many can claim to "own" an army.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Pocos pueden afirmar "poseer" un ejército.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: An apprentice from the revered Palace of the Wizard Caliph.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Un aprendiz del venerado Palacio del Califa Hechicero.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Born in the dunes, some will never see him as their equal.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Nacido en las dunas, algunos nunca lo verán como su igual.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Smoke and loud bangs emanate day and night from this one's tent.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Humo y ruidos fuertes emanan día y noche de la tienda de este individuo.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: He has more in common with the beasts than his fellow man.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Tiene más en común con las bestias que con sus compañeros humanos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: He demands all under his command train with the bow.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Exige que todos bajo su mando entrenen con el arco.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A hero feared and renowned in much of Araby.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Un héroe temido y renombrado en gran parte de Arabia.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Those proven proficient in magic are gifted the Rattlesnake Staff by the Wizard Caliph, it is the mark of any good Arabyan sorcerer.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Aquellos que han demostrado su destreza en la magia reciben el Bastón de Serpiente del Califa Hechicero, es la marca de cualquier buen hechicero árabe.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A fine-blade presented to Arabyan Warriors who have proved themselves in battle, gaining them respect from all.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Una espada fina presentada a los Guerreros Árabes que han demostrado su valía en batalla, ganándoles respeto de todos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Endless days in the dunes has left this one dogged and burly.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Días interminables en las dunas han dejado a este ser tenaz y corpulento.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Fine heavy armour, though its weight stifles movement.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Una armadura pesada de gran calidad, aunque su peso sofoca el movimiento.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: His mind is as immovable as his body.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Su mente es tan inmovable como su cuerpo.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Moving tirelessly through the sands of Araby.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Moviéndose incansablemente a través de las arenas de Arabia.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The Golden Magus had fought against the Vampire Coast bitterly, and now makes use of their necromantic arts against them.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El Mago Dorado luchó contra la Costa Vampira de manera feroz, y ahora hace uso de sus artes nigrománticas contra ellos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Due to his charisma and his power over the Djinns, he managed to unite the nomadic tribes of the desert and formed the Sultanate of Araby.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Debido a su carisma y su poder sobre los Djinns, logró unificar las tribus nómadas del desierto y formar el Sultanato de Arabia.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The relentless drive and fury of the elemental spirits, harnessed for the protection of this ward’s bearer.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El impulso implacable y la furia de los espíritus elementales, aprovechados para la protección del portador de esta protección.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: In the arsenals of the Sultans are countless powerful guns capable of firing devastating volleys.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: En los arsenales de los Sultanes hay incontables armas poderosas capaces de disparar devastadoras descargas.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: They call him the beast whisperer, for these creatures would truly die for him.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Lo llaman el susurrador de bestias, porque estas criaturas realmente morirían por él.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The sand dunes are so large that a man can only cross them with his trusty mount.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Las dunas de arena son tan grandes que un hombre solo puede cruzarlas con su fiel montura.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Hit and run tactics work especially well in the desert. That's why the horsemen of Araby are particularly skilled marksmen.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Las tácticas de golpe y huida funcionan especialmente bien en el desierto. Por eso, los jinetes de Arabia son tiradores especialmente habilidosos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Years of training and fighting in the scorching desert sun creates exceptionally tough fighters.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Años de entrenamiento y lucha bajo el abrasador sol del desierto crean luchadores excepcionalmente duros.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Warriors of great armies are decorated in ornate armour taken from the Sultan's personal armory, even the slaves!
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Los guerreros de grandes ejércitos están decorados con armaduras ornamentadas tomadas del arsenal personal del Sultán, ¡incluso los esclavos!

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: You are wise in the ways of magic and have much to teach others.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Eres sabio en los caminos de la magia y tienes mucho que enseñar a los demás.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The powerful Djinns and various other monstrous creatures are fielded to destroy the enemies of Araby.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Los poderosos Djinns y otras criaturas monstruosas son desplegados para destruir a los enemigos de Arabia.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: You have seen many brothers fall in battle, for that is what the nomads are, my brothers.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Has visto caer a muchos hermanos en batalla, porque eso es lo que son los nómadas, mis hermanos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Veterans among the settled peoples, or "hadir", of Araby are able to be bestowed with titles and finery befitting their contribution to these great lands.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Los veteranos entre los pueblos establecidos, o "hadir", de Arabia pueden recibir títulos y adornos que corresponden a su contribución a estas grandes tierras.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The finest horses in Araby, bred for their endurance and fiery temperament, barded for further protection.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Los mejores caballos de Arabia, criados por su resistencia y su temperamento fogoso, equipados con bardas para una mayor protección.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Whether out of fear or conviction, this leader is able to rally a relentless force behind him.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Ya sea por miedo o convicción, este líder es capaz de reunir una fuerza imparable detrás de él.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The finest horses in Araby, bred for their endurance and fiery temperament, barded for further protection.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Los mejores caballos de Arabia, criados por su resistencia y su temperamento fogoso, equipados con bardas para una mayor protección.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The mount of any self-respecting Arabyan gentleman.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: La montura de cualquier caballero árabe que se respete a sí mismo.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A Djinn bound to a piece of furniture to make it fly.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Un Djinn atado a una alfombra para hacerla volar.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: La montura de cualquier caballero árabe que se respete a sí mismo.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A Djinn bound to a piece of furniture to make it fly.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Un Djinn atado a una alfombra para hacerla volar.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Once of the Sultan's artillery legions. Though now an independent trader, those ties are hard to break.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Antes formaba parte de las legiones de artillería del Sultán. Aunque ahora es un comerciante independiente, esos lazos son difíciles de romper.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Many masters of the continent spanning caravans come from the peasant oases or the slums of the Araby's mighty cities.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Muchos de los maestros de las caravanas que atraviesan el continente provienen de oasis campesinos o de los barrios bajos de las poderosas ciudades de Arabia.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Crack open a few kegs of Tialva or Arag and you've got some friends for life.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: ¿Abrir unos barriles de Tialva o Arag y tener amigos de por vida? Claro, si ignoras la serie de robos sin resolver que dejan a su paso.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Fangweasels, Bonechewers, Indrikas, Lake-Lions? All out of stock, but could I interest you in this Giant Vulture?
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: ¿Comadrejas dentadas, Mordedores de Huesos, Indrikas, Leones del Lago? Todos fuera de stock, pero ¿te interesaría este Buitre Gigante?

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Running this caravan is the most contact his tribe has had with the world in years.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Dirigir esta caravana es el mayor contacto que su tribu ha tenido con el mundo en años.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The caravan and its master spends a lot of time in the Land of Chivalry, to the point that he prefers the company of foreigners to his homeland.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: La caravana y su maestro pasan mucho tiempo en la Tierra de la Caballerosidad, hasta el punto de que prefiere la compañía de extranjeros a la de su tierra natal.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A secretive history allows him to call upon veteran troops who perhaps served him in the past.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Un historial secreto le permite llamar a tropas veteranas que quizás lo hayan servido en el pasado.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: This caravan is a front for the Cult of the Djinns, hoping to spread their message to the wider world.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Esta caravana es una tapadera para el Culto de los Djinns, con la esperanza de difundir su mensaje al mundo exterior.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Did you know that elephants are the world's 89th largest land animal?
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: ¿Sabías que los elefantes son el 89º animal terrestre más grande del mundo?

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Fire hot, fire good.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Fuego caliente, fuego bueno.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Now did I buy the powder from the Dwarfs or the Cathayans? Ah well, it probably doesn't matter.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Ahora, ¿compré la pólvora a los Enanos o a los Cathayanos? Bueno, probablemente no importe.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Born and raised in Ras Karim, he spent his early days walking up and down the Street of the Scholars. Some of that ingenuity must have rubbed off on him.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Nacido y criado en Ras Karim, pasó sus primeros días caminando arriba y abajo por la Calle de los Eruditos. Algo de esa ingenio debió haberse impregnado en él.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: According to the Kitab al-Filaha al-Martekiyya, nasty weather can be predicted and avoided by careful observation of wind movements, the lunar phases, and planetary astral alterations.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Según el Kitab al-Filaha al-Martekiyya, el mal tiempo puede preverse y evitarse con una cuidadosa observación de los movimientos del viento, las fases lunares y las alteraciones astrales planetarias.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: This man has dedicated his life to the Djinn and follows the teachings of the Cult to the letter.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Este hombre ha dedicado su vida a los Djinns y sigue las enseñanzas del Culto al pie de la letra.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: In Araby, reputation is a powerful tool, and those favoured by sultans and emirs will be able to recruit quality troops.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: En Arabia, la reputación es una herramienta poderosa, y aquellos favorecidos por sultanes y emires podrán reclutar tropas de calidad.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: A band of corsairs and their captain, turned to a life of honest work? Sure, if you ignore string of unsolved burglaries they leave in their wake.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: ¿Una banda de corsarios y su capitán, convertidos a una vida de trabajo honesto? Claro, si ignoras la serie de robos sin resolver que dejan a su paso.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: An entourage of laborers and eunuchs accompany this caravan.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Una comitiva de obreros y eunucos acompaña esta caravana.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Brought up in the Southlands, with an intimate knowledge of its denizens and geography.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Criado en las Tierras del Sur, con un conocimiento íntimo de sus habitantes y su geografía.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Of the Tuareg tribe. Their typical fight-for-coin lifestyle doesn't suit him, so he's taken to trading. There's still a lot of fighting though.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: De la tribu Tuareg. Su estilo de vida típico, luchar por dinero, no le conviene, así que se ha dedicado al comercio. Aún así, sigue habiendo mucha lucha.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: With this unrestrained lifestyle, the Prince of Pleasure might one day come to him.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Con este estilo de vida desenfrenado, el Príncipe del Placer podría llegar un día a él.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The caster calls on the elements of the desert and draws upon the fortune they can bestow.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El lanzador invoca los elementos del desierto y aprovecha la fortuna que pueden otorgar.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: By invoking the Element of Fire, one of the caster's hands becomes burning hot, which he can use to smite enemies.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Al invocar el Elemento del Fuego, una de las manos del hechicero se vuelve ardientemente caliente, la cual puede usar para golpear a sus enemigos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: By invoking the Element of Fire, one of the caster's hands becomes burning hot, which he can use to smite enemies.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Al invocar el Elemento del Fuego, una de las manos del hechicero se vuelve ardientemente caliente, la cual puede usar para golpear a sus enemigos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The sorcerer channels the immense power of the Djinn through his own body and lays a terrible curse upon his foes.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El hechicero canaliza el inmenso poder de los Djinn a través de su propio cuerpo y lanza una terrible maldición sobre sus enemigos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The sorcerer channels the immense power of the Djinn through his own body and lays a terrible curse upon his foes.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El hechicero canaliza el inmenso poder de los Djinn a través de su propio cuerpo y lanza una terrible maldición sobre sus enemigos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The sorcerer creates the illusion of a huge host of fearsome warriors, bearing down inexorably upon his startled foes.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El hechicero crea la ilusión de un enorme ejército de temibles guerreros, que se abalanza inexorablemente sobre sus sorprendidos enemigos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: The sorcerer creates the illusion of a huge host of fearsome warriors, bearing down inexorably upon his startled foes.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: El hechicero crea la ilusión de un enorme ejército de temibles guerreros, que se abalanza inexorablemente sobre sus sorprendidos enemigos.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: By invoking the Element of Water, moisture rises up from the very rocks and sand, turning the ground into deadly quicksand.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Al invocar el Elemento del Agua, la humedad asciende de las propias rocas y la arena, convirtiendo el suelo en peligrosas arenas movedizas.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: By invoking the Element of Water, moisture rises up from the very rocks and sand, turning the ground into deadly quicksand.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Al invocar el Elemento del Agua, la humedad asciende de las propias rocas y la arena, convirtiendo el suelo en peligrosas arenas movedizas.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Commanding the Desert Spirit of Da'ru'de, the sorcerer engulfs his foes in a swirling cloud of choking sand and dust.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Comandando al Espíritu del Desierto de Da'ru'de, el hechicero envuelve a sus enemigos en una nube giratoria de arena y polvo que los asfixia.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Commanding the Desert Spirit of Da'ru'de, the sorcerer engulfs his foes in a swirling cloud of choking sand and dust.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Comandando al Espíritu del Desierto de Da'ru'de, el hechicero envuelve a sus enemigos en una nube giratoria de arena y polvo que los asfixia.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Bright beams of burning energy leap from the sorcerer's eyes and scythe through all before him.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Rayos brillantes de energía ardiente saltan de los ojos del hechicero y cortan todo lo que tienen ante él.

character_skills_localised_description_o.value_original: Bright beams of burning energy leap from the sorcerer's eyes and scythe through all before him.
character_skills_localised_description_o.value_translated: Rayos brillantes de energía ardiente saltan de los ojos del hechicero y cortan todo lo que tienen ante él.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Elephants are unstoppable beasts. Trained on the battlefield, they lead Araby's leaders to war, wiping out everything that gets in their way.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Los elefantes son bestias imparables. Entrenados en el campo de batalla, llevan a los líderes de Arabia a la guerra, arrasando con todo lo que se interpone en su camino.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: The finest horses in Araby, bred for their endurance and fiery temperament, barded for further protection.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Los mejores caballos de Arabia, criados por su resistencia y su temperamento fogoso, equipados con bardas para una mayor protección.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: These noble beasts absorb the sun's heat, transmuting it into the burning light that flows over their skin like ripples of brightest flame.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Estas nobles bestias absorben el calor del sol, transformándolo en la luz ardiente que fluye sobre su piel como ondas de la llama más brillante.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: These noble beasts absorb the sun's heat, transmuting it into the burning light that flows over their skin like ripples of brightest flame.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Estas nobles bestias absorben el calor del sol, transformándolo en la luz ardiente que fluye sobre su piel como ondas de la llama más brillante.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: These noble beasts absorb the sun's heat, transmuting it into the burning light that flows over their skin like ripples of brightest flame.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Estas nobles bestias absorben el calor del sol, transformándolo en la luz ardiente que fluye sobre su piel como ondas de la llama más brillante.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Even from within their vessels the Djinn will protect their masters.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Incluso desde dentro de sus vasijas, los Djinn protegerán a sus maestros.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Even the smallest acts of kindness can mean to world to someone in need.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Incluso los actos más pequeños de bondad pueden significar el mundo para alguien que lo necesite.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Honour is everything!
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: ¡El honor es todo!

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Pride comes before the fall.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: El orgullo precede a la caída.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Some people simply can't get enough.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Algunas personas simplemente no se cansan.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: In the eyes of the brave, danger gleams like sunshine.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: En los ojos de los valientes, el peligro brilla como el sol.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: This one has gained deep knowledge about local cultures and politics.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Este ha adquirido un profundo conocimiento sobre las culturas y políticas locales.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: A skilled assassin is a cold-hearted killer and merciless murderer.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Un asesino hábil es un asesino de corazón frío y un despiadado asesino.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Deceit is a perfectly acceptable means of attack.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: El engaño es un medio perfectamente aceptable de ataque.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: People say you can't trust him, he'll betray anybody for the right price.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: La gente dice que no se puede confiar en él, traicionará a cualquiera por el precio adecuado.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: This being has a plan - not just a game plan, but a master plan to achieve his long-term aims.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Este ser tiene un plan, no solo un plan de juego, sino un plan maestro para alcanzar sus objetivos a largo plazo.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: This one ensures that those captured in battle wished they'd died on the field, so great is the cruelty that awaits them.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Este asegura que aquellos capturados en batalla desearían haber muerto en el campo, tan grande es la crueldad que les espera.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Now you see them, now you don’t… and now you’re seeing double.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Ahora los ves, ahora no… y ahora los ves por duplicado.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: When you are the target of a Hashishi, you'll never know it until it is too late.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Cuando eres el objetivo de un Hashishi, nunca lo sabrás hasta que sea demasiado tarde.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: They won't feel a thing... unless you want them to.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: No sentirán nada... a menos que tú quieras que lo hagan.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Palace Guards are among the most prestigious soldiers, tasked with the protection of the Arabyan Nobles.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Los Guardias del Palacio están entre los soldados más prestigiosos, encargados de la protección de los nobles árabes.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: It is important to stay grounded when climbing up the chain of command.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Es importante mantenerse firme cuando se asciende en la cadena de mando.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Some only fight for fame and glory, becoming well-trained champions in the process.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Algunos solo luchan por fama y gloria, convirtiéndose en campeones bien entrenados en el proceso.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Elephants are unstoppable beasts. Trained on the battlefield, they lead Araby's leaders to war, wiping out everything that gets in their way.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Los elefantes son bestias imparables. Entrenados en el campo de batalla, llevan a los líderes de Arabia a la guerra, arrasando con todo lo que se interpone en su camino.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: The finest horses in Araby, bred for their endurance and fiery temperament, barded for further protection.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Los mejores caballos de Arabia, criados por su resistencia y su temperamento fogoso, equipados con bardas para una mayor protección.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: The finest horses in Araby, bred for their endurance and fiery temperament, barded for further protection.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Los mejores caballos de Arabia, criados por su resistencia y su temperamento fogoso, equipados con bardas para una mayor protección.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: Armed with long-barrelled arquebus of Arabyan design, the endless deserts have taught these men the value of marksmanship and an accurate firearm.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Armados con arcabuces de cañón largo de diseño árabe, los interminables desiertos han enseñado a estos hombres el valor de la puntería y un arma de fuego precisa.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: After years of service and loyalty, a Hashishi will receive the mark of the brotherhood.
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Después de años de servicio y lealtad, un Hashishi recibirá la marca de la hermandad.

character_skills_localised_description_r.value_original: One major advantage the camel provides for these mounted archers is simply a better angle for their arrows to aim true than from their horse counterparts. Albeit, mounted archery on a camel is no easy task!
character_skills_localised_description_r.value_translated: Una de las principales ventajas que el camello proporciona a estos arqueros montados es simplemente un mejor ángulo para que sus flechas apunten con precisión, en comparación con sus contrapartes a caballo. ¡Aunque, la arquería montada sobre camello no es tarea fácil!

character_trait_levels_colour_text_ovn_a.value_original: Twice a ruler, twice a failure. Princess Fatandira has learnt the hard way that the crown will never be her destiny.
character_trait_levels_colour_text_ovn_a.value_translated: Dos veces gobernante, dos veces un fracaso. La Princesa Fatandira ha aprendido por las malas que la corona nunca será su destino.

character_trait_levels_colour_text_ovn_a.value_original: Whether he was defeated by an enemy or turned against by his own Djinn slaves is unknown, but the Golden Magus will no longer pester the sea with his cruel petulance and eccentricity.
character_trait_levels_colour_text_ovn_a.value_translated: Si fue derrotado por un enemigo o traicionado por sus propios esclavos Djinns es desconocido, pero el Mago Dorado ya no molestará más al mar con su cruel petulancia y excentricidad.

character_trait_levels_colour_text_ovn_a.value_original: Mighty Jaffar lies dead once again. For how long, no one knows for certain...
character_trait_levels_colour_text_ovn_a.value_translated: El poderoso Jaffar yace muerto una vez más. Por cuánto tiempo, nadie sabe con certeza...

culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_original: Resettle||With no regions currently under your control, you have the option to settle your army here.
culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_translated: Reasentar||Sin ninguna región actualmente bajo tu control, tienes la opción de asentar tu ejército aquí.

culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_original: Raze||All buildings are destroyed and the settlement is torched. The previous owners will like you a lot less.
culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_translated: Arrasar||Todos los edificios son destruidos y el asentamiento es incendiado. Los antiguos propietarios te querrán mucho menos.

culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_original: Sack||You do not capture the settlement but instead steal wealth and damage buildings. Todos los cautivos son esclavizados, [[img:icon_public_order]][[/img]]{{tr:hp_campaign_public_order_term}} se reduce, y los antiguos propietarios te querrán mucho menos.

culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_original: Do Nothing||Leave the settlement as it stands.
culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_translated: No hacer nada||Deja el asentamiento tal como está.

culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_translated: Arrasar||Todos los edificios son destruidos y el asentamiento es incendiado. Los antiguos propietarios te querrán mucho menos.

culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_original: Restore Numas||Return ownership of Numas to its rightful owner.
culture_settlement_occupation_options_to.value_translated: Restaurar Numas||Devuelve la propiedad de Numas a su legítimo dueño.

cultures_frontend_description_ovn_araby.value_original: Araby is an ancient realm of Men that lies far to the south of the nations of the Old World, home to cities and savage tribes of desert nomads alike. A strange and exotic country, it is ruled by powerful sultans and desert sheikhs. It rises across vast expanses of desert, its cities are located on the Coast of Araby, to the west, and to the northern borders of the Southlands. Its merchants travel and trade extensively throughout the world, establishing trade networks that span every sea and nation. Their society is notoriously focused on commerce and piracy, both of which, carried out on a global scale, bring them fabulous wealth: their sultans and caliphs are said to be richer than the Dwarfs. This trade is carried beyond the sea thanks to its dhows, fast ships with triangular sails. They have a remarkable interest in science, medicine, and magical knowledge, and their nobles invest large sums to fund research of all kinds.\\n\\nOn many occasions, the Arabyans have tried to establish themselves outside their homes, occupying territories such as Sartosa or the Border Princes but have been pushed back each time. Perhaps it is time for a strong ruler to once again set about conquering the world for the Sultanate.
cultures_frontend_description_ovn_araby.value_translated: Arabia es un antiguo reino de los Hombres que se encuentra muy al sur de las naciones del Viejo Mundo, hogar tanto de ciudades como de tribus salvajes de nómadas del desierto. Un país extraño y exótico, está gobernado por poderosos sultanes y jeques del desierto. Se extiende a través de vastas extensiones de desierto, con sus ciudades situadas en la Costa de Arabia, al oeste, y en las fronteras del norte de las Tierras del Sur. Sus mercaderes viajan y comercian extensamente por todo el mundo, estableciendo redes comerciales que abarcan todos los mares y naciones. Su sociedad es notoriamente centrada en el comercio y la piratería, ambos llevados a cabo a escala global, lo que les otorga fabulosa riqueza: se dice que sus sultanes y califas son más ricos que los Enanos. Este comercio se lleva más allá del mar gracias a sus dhows, barcos rápidos con velas triangulares. Tienen un notable interés en la ciencia, la medicina y el conocimiento mágico, y sus nobles invierten grandes sumas para financiar la investigación en todo tipo de campos. \\n\\nEn muchas ocasiones, los árabes han intentado establecerse fuera de su hogar, ocupando territorios como Sartosa o los Príncipes Fronterizos, pero han sido rechazados cada vez. Tal vez sea hora de que un gobernante fuerte se disponga nuevamente a conquistar el mundo para el Sultanato.

cultures_subcultures_battle_playstyle_de.value_original: Araby has access to a wide variety of units, but of rather mediocre quality, especially in infantry. To fully develop their strength, they use a combined-arms approach. They rely mainly on their skirmishers, fast cavalry and powerful Elephant and Djinn units to win.
cultures_subcultures_battle_playstyle_de.value_translated: Arabia tiene acceso a una amplia variedad de unidades, pero de calidad bastante mediocre, especialmente en infantería. Para desarrollar completamente su fuerza, utilizan un enfoque de armas combinadas. Dependen principalmente de sus exploradores, caballería ligera y poderosas unidades de Elefantes y Djinns para ganar.

dilemmas_localised_description_ovn_dilem.value_original: My most glorious leader, an excavation has uncovered a great tomb with many riches, should we begin securing the treasures?
dilemmas_localised_description_ovn_dilem.value_translated: Mi más glorioso líder, una excavación ha descubierto una gran tumba con muchas riquezas, ¿debemos comenzar a asegurar los tesoros?

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: We hear our fellow Arabyan caravan before we see it, great drums pounding on the backs of elephants, oud lutes plucking sweet notes, and the sound of Arabyan marching songs splitting the air. The caravan master scoffs, for surely this lesser caravan cannot match our wealth and glory. But then we see them, riders on Flying Carpets! Outrageous! How dare this lesser caravan have such prestigious allies!?
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Oímos a nuestra caravana arábiga antes de verla: enormes tambores sobre lomos de elefantes, laúdes oud que arrancan dulces notas y el sonido de cánticos marciales arábigos que parten el aire. El líder de nuestra caravana se burla, pues seguramente esta caravana menor no podrá igualar nuestra riqueza y gloria. Pero entonces los vemos: ¡jinetes en Alfombras Voladoras! ¡Inconcebible! ¿Cómo se atreven estos don nadie a contar con aliados tan prestigiosos?

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: As we come to a desert outpost, we see a terrible sight. The guards are all missing, and blood is everywhere! As we search the outpost to discover what could have caused such a tragedy, the men shout in alarm! A swarm of furious Rope Djinns, angered at having been bound in such a manner, ready themselves to attack!
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Al acercarnos a un puesto avanzado del desierto, contemplamos una escena espantosa. ¡No hay guardias y la sangre lo cubre todo! Al buscar alguna pista de la tragedia, los hombres gritan alarmados. ¡Una horda de furiosas Cuerdas Djinn, irritadas por haber sido atadas de tal manera, se preparan para atacar!

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: While traveling through foreign lands, your caravan encounters a local force equipped with fine blades of ensorcelled Arabyan steel. Very familiar blades, as a matter of fact. Upon inquiring about the situation, you discover that these blades were recovered from an Arabyan shipwreck their master recently looted. One of your merchant vessels, it seems, lost at sea not too long ago. By rights, these blades are yours.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Mientras avanzamos por tierras extranjeras, nuestra caravana encuentra una fuerza local equipada con finas hojas forjadas en acero arábigo hechizado. De hecho, nos resultan demasiado familiares. Al investigar la situación, descubrimos que estas hojas fueron recuperadas de un naufragio arábigo que su amo saqueó recientemente. Por lo visto, uno de nuestros barcos mercantes se hundió hace poco. Por derecho, estas armas nos pertenecen.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Our Caravan has come upon a minor Bretonnian Errantry led by a Noble bearing the familial name of one of the original Bretonnian Crusaders who invaded our shores! We have a chance to avenge our Ancestors deaths by the hands of these Savages or we can continue on our path.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: ¡Nuestra Caravana se ha topado con una pequeña partida de la Bretonia Peregrina, liderada por un Noble que porta el apellido familiar de uno de los cruzados bretonianos originales que invadieron nuestras costas! Tenemos la oportunidad de vengar la muerte de nuestros ancestros a manos de estos salvajes o podemos continuar nuestro camino.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: A lonely Caravan has been spotted trundling through nearby land, bearing the banners of Cathay. No doubt the products of the so-called Celestial Empire would be worth snatching for ourselves, yet such spoils are not likely to lie unguarded.\\n\\nA choice between killing or caution. It seems the answer is clear...
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Se ha avistado una Caravana solitaria atravesando tierras cercanas, con los estandartes de Cathay. Sin duda los productos del llamado Imperio Celestial valdrían la pena arrebatárselos, aunque no es probable que semejante botín esté desprotegido.\\n\\nUna elección entre matar o ser cautos. Parece que la respuesta está clara...

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: We spotted a smoke column in the distance, upon further inspection we noticed that it was moving, specifically it's moving towards us: it's a Chaos Dwarf convoy, lead by a priest of Hashut, upon their approach, they make their intentions clear: they are looking to trade, and they won't take no for an answer.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Divisamos una columna de humo a lo lejos; al investigar, notamos que se mueve, y concretamente se acerca hacia nosotros: se trata de un convoy de Enanos del Caos, liderado por un sacerdote de Hashut. Al acercarse, dejan claras sus intenciones: buscan comerciar y no aceptarán un “no” por respuesta.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: It is no secret that the southern seas are home to many hidden coves and islands where the pirates of Sartosa like to hide their booty. As it happens you spot a pirate crew digging around on a shore not too far away from you. Fighting them might not be part of your route but it might get you whatever they are looking for…
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: No es secreto que los mares del sur albergan muchas calas e islas ocultas donde los piratas de Sartosa suelen esconder su botín. Parece que divisamos una tripulación pirata cavando en una costa no muy lejana. Pelear con ellos quizá no forme parte de nuestro itinerario, pero podría darnos lo que están buscando…

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Your caravan is halted by a far-flung Black Ark, seemingly here for piracy. Eyeing your slaves, and desperate for anything, they make a deal. They will take some of your slaves, and you will take some of their finest soldiers.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Tu caravana se ve detenida por una Arca Negra lejana, aparentemente aquí por piratería. Observan tus esclavos y, en su desesperación, proponen un trato: tomarán algunos de tus esclavos, y tú obtendrás a cambio algunos de sus mejores soldados.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Our Caravans are used to dealing with Corsairs from our own shores, but this time some intrepid Corsair Captain has organised a large force to halt our progress and demands we hand over tribute to be allowed safe passage.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Nuestras Caravanas están acostumbradas a tratar con Corsarios de nuestras propias costas, pero esta vez un capitán corsario decidido ha organizado una gran fuerza para detenernos y exige que le entreguemos un tributo a cambio de dejarnos pasar a salvo.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: As our caravan traverses past a once empty ruin they notice that there is a gleaming light far down the road. The caravan approaches this light but it soon resolves into the image of an army on the march. Rank upon rank of skeletons march in perfect lockstep and hulking beasts of bone are spotted behind them. It appears they are marching this way and they most definitely see the caravan.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Al atravesar un ruinoso paraje que estaba vacío tiempo atrás, notamos un brillo al fondo del camino. Al acercarse, resulta ser la imagen de un ejército en marcha. Hilera tras hilera de esqueletos avanzan en perfecta sincronía y se distinguen grandes bestias óseas a sus espaldas. Parece que marchan en esta dirección y sin duda ven nuestra caravana.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: A wandering Caravan of Dwarf has entered our site. Should we attack them for a fresh new set of slaves?
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Una Caravana errante de Enanos ha llegado a nuestro campo de visión. ¿Deberíamos atacarlos para obtener un nuevo lote de esclavos frescos?

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: As we track across the lands near the mountains you spotted a Dwarfen caravan. Upon the approach one Thane approached and wishes to follow along with our caravan because of grudges against members of his current group. But the sharp eyes amongst you also notice that the caravan also brings with them plenty of treasure, and for those with a thirst for more gold this is easy pickings.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Mientras avanzamos por tierras cercanas a las montañas, avistamos una caravana enana. Al acercarnos, se presenta un Thane que desea unirse a nuestra caravana por rencores contra miembros de su propio grupo. Pero los ojos más ágiles se dan cuenta de que la caravana también transporta mucho tesoro, y para quienes ansíen más oro, esto es una oportunidad fácil.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: We have stumbled upon a band of Soldiers of Fortune from the Northern Empire. While their customs and beliefs are weird, especially their dogmatic belief in their man god ‘Sigmar’, they can be reliable soldiers. Let's hope they learn to wash themselves properly while in our employ if we hire them.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Nos hemos topado con un grupo de Soldados de Fortuna del Imperio del norte. Sus costumbres y creencias son extrañas, sobre todo esa fe dogmática en su dios-hombre “Sigmar”, pero pueden ser soldados confiables. Esperemos que aprendan a asearse apropiadamente mientras estén a nuestro servicio, si los contratamos.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Signs of a troop column have been spotted ahead. Judging by the tracks, it looks as though this force has been moving without sleep or pause. Cresting the next hill, the gleam of bone and gold can be seen throughout the army. A host of Tomb Kings, richly adorned, is marching through this area. Their destination is unclear, but their opulence is not. We could descend upon them, and claim their riches for ourselves!
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Se han divisado señales de una columna de tropas más adelante. A juzgar por las huellas, parece que esta fuerza ha avanzado sin descanso ni sueño. Al coronar la siguiente colina, el brillo de huesos y oro destaca en todo el ejército. Un ejército de Reyes Funerarios, ricamente ataviado, marcha por la zona. Su destino es incierto, pero su opulencia no. ¡Podríamos descender sobre ellos y reclamar sus riquezas!

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Strange mists surround our caravan as we are forced to push the wagons through a muddy mire. The beasts of burden are ill at ease as bloated flies hover over us like buzzards circling a desert meal and the thick, humid air makes each labored breath harder to endure. Just when we thought things couldn’t get any worse, a shrill cry is heard over the din of swamplife and a ululating horde of one-eyed monsters emerge from the waters with crude weapons and vile magic in hand.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Una bruma extraña rodea nuestra caravana mientras nos vemos obligados a arrastrar los carros a través de un lodazal. Las bestias de carga están inquietas mientras moscas hinchadas revolotean sobre nosotros como buitres que acechan un festín desértico, y el aire espeso y húmedo hace que cada respiración sea más pesada. Cuando pensábamos que no podía empeorar, se escucha un grito agudo entre la algarabía de la vida pantanosa y una horda de monstruos tuertos emerge de las aguas, armados con armas rudimentarias y magia vil.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: It seems like there was a big battle nearby, we can take some of the remnants or use the equipment to empower the existing troops.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Parece que hubo una gran batalla cerca; podemos tomar algunos de los restos o usar el equipo para fortalecer a las tropas actuales.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: While traveling on the road our caravan spots a lumbering beast hauling a ramshackle wagon crewed by a scrawny bunch of Gnoblars. The wagon pulls alongside of us and the head of this odd band, a spectacled Gnoblar wearing a turban of Arabyan fashion, speaks to our caravan leader of his journeys throughout these lands. He eyes our cargo the entire time and he asks for some of it to fund his latest invention, the Gnoblar Gnose Gnourisher. He offers you the services of his guards in return for your shiny scrap.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Mientras avanza la caravana, ve a lo lejos una bestia enorme que arrastra un carro destartalado ocupado por un puñado de Gnoblars escuálidos. El carro se nos acerca y el jefe de este extraño grupo, un Gnoblar con anteojos y un turbante de estilo arábigo, habla con nuestro líder de la caravana acerca de sus viajes por estas tierras. No deja de mirar nuestra carga y pide parte de ella para financiar su más reciente invento, el Gnoblar Gnose Gnourisher. Ofrece los servicios de sus guardias a cambio de nuestro brillo.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: The High Elves are infamous for thinking of themselves as the guardians of the world, this part included. A force sent from Ulthuan to one of their far-flung colonies happens upon your caravan and makes it very clear that you are to pay a tax to the Phoenix court for conducting trade here. Of course, some handlers would have to be assigned to you for the rest of your journeys too to keep you “safe”. They don’t seem to give us much of a choice...
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Los Altos Elfos son famosos por creerse guardianes del mundo, incluyendo esta región. Una fuerza enviada desde Ulthuan a una de sus colonias remotas se topa con nuestra caravana y deja muy claro que debemos pagar un tributo a la corte Fénix por comerciar aquí. Por supuesto, también tendríamos que llevar “escoltas” por el resto de nuestros viajes para mantenernos “a salvo”. No parecen darnos mucha opción…

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Our Caravan has been halted by a force of High Elves who demand we pay the customary Tribute to the Phoenix King, the Elves think these trade-routes are their property and are citing all sorts of ancient treaties to prove their claim.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Nuestra Caravana ha sido detenida por una fuerza de Altos Elfos que exigen el pago del habitual Tributo al Rey Fénix; los Elfos creen que estas rutas comerciales son de su propiedad y citan toda clase de tratados antiguos para justificar su reclamo.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Traversing realms is hungry work if these Daemons we've encountered are to be believed. You could choose to sate their gluttonous appetites in the hopes of avoiding a fight. Yet, on the other hand, death would solve their hunger too…
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Atravesar reinos es un trabajo hambriento si hacemos caso a estos Demonios con los que nos topamos. Podríamos saciar su apetito glotón para evitar un combate; por otro lado, la muerte también resolvería su hambre…

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Unfortunate wretches of many races travel the sea to gather wealth. Yet while out on assignment, even our Caravan knows not to pass up the opportunity to attain more of the "right tools" for the job, having encountered a High Elf host from whom much profit could be forcibly reaped – both in long-limbed Labourers and loot reaped from beardless corpses.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Desgraciadas criaturas de muchas razas surcan los mares en busca de riqueza. Pero incluso nuestra Caravana sabe que no debe dejar pasar la oportunidad de conseguir más “herramientas adecuadas” para la labor. Hemos encontrado un ejército de Altos Elfos, de los que podríamos sacar gran ganancia —en mano de obra de brazos largos y botín de cadáveres lampiños.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: A great artifact of dark magic has come to our grasp. However, we need to decide which equipment we should empower to give the Caravan the greatest chance of successfully repelling any threats.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Ha llegado a nuestras manos un gran artefacto de magia oscura. Sin embargo, debemos decidir qué equipamiento fortalecer para darle a la Caravana la mejor oportunidad de repeler cualquier amenaza.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: The strength of an Ogre is unmatched anywhere! At least, that's what this group of rotund mercenaries assured us when offering to guard our trade Caravan on its route. Their claim is ridiculous but the extra muscle wouldn't go amiss. Ogres' services, however, certainly would not come free of charge.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: ¡La fuerza de un Ogro no tiene igual en ningún lugar! Al menos, eso afirman este grupo de mercenarios rollizos cuando se ofrecen a proteger nuestra Caravana comercial. Su pretensión es ridícula, pero un músculo adicional no vendría mal. Sin embargo, los servicios de un Ogro no son gratis.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Without warning, a sudden chill rushes through the bones. A torrent of whispers floods the heads of the warriors, all repeating the same thing.\\n\\n[[i]]"Make a sacrifice, and overwhelming power shall be yours…"[[/i]]
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Sin previo aviso, un escalofrío atraviesa los huesos. Una ola de susurros inunda las mentes de los guerreros, repitiendo lo mismo.\\n\\n[[i]]“Haz un sacrificio, y un poder abrumador será tuyo…”[[/i]]

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: The Caravan Master scouts a quicker route which would make up for the lost time. However, looking at the weather, that shortcut would result in some damaged 'goods'.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: El Maestro de la Caravana ha hallado una ruta más rápida que compensaría el tiempo perdido. Sin embargo, al ver el clima, ese atajo supondría que parte de la “mercancía” sufra daños.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: This ship is filled with rats! Unless we have dealt with them sooner or we will have to make a stop to refill our supplies. Maybe we need to track them all and kill them.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: ¡Este barco está lleno de ratas! A menos que lidiemos con ellas pronto, tendremos que detenernos para reponer suministros. Tal vez debamos rastrearlas y matarlas a todas.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Fog has descended around our Caravan. The smell is putrid and shuffling shapes can be glimpsed in the haze. This land around us teems with their shambling forms; we have stumbled, unwittingly, into the domain of the Undead. These creatures can be confronted head-on and the wretches put down for good or, alternatively, we can order some of our number to distract them while we make our escape, though they will ultimately have no hope against the necrotic masses.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Una niebla ha caído sobre nuestra Caravana. El olor es pútrido y, en la penumbra, se vislumbran figuras que se arrastran. Esta tierra está repleta de sus formas tambaleantes; hemos entrado, sin querer, en el dominio de los No Muertos. Podemos enfrentarlos de frente y acabar con esos miserables para siempre, o bien ordenar que algunos de los nuestros los distraigan mientras escapamos; aunque esos pobres no tendrán esperanza contra las masas necróticas.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Along the road, some of your caravaneers are ambushed, the sky being blotted out with smoke and chittering filling the air. They offer usage of their Underways to speed up your journey, if only for 1300 gold and some of your goods.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: En el camino, algunos integrantes de tu caravana son emboscados; el cielo se oscurece con humo y suena un murmullo constante. Ofrecen usar sus Subterráneos para acelerar tu viaje, si pagas 1300 de oro y parte de tus bienes.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: It is said that our caravan leader is a paramour of the famed Princess of Pavona herself, Lucrezzia Belladonna. After their last meeting she promised a lavish gift in the future and now a delegation of mercenaries from Pavona has found our caravan and they present a gift from their employer.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Dicen que nuestro líder de Caravana es el amante de la famosa Princesa de Pavona, la propia Lucrezzia Belladonna. Tras su último encuentro, ella prometió un regalo suntuoso para el futuro; ahora, un grupo de mercenarios de Pavona nos ha hallado y trae un presente de su parte.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Stealth is possibly not the strong suit of our would-be ambushers, who visibly await our Caravan from some rather questionable 'hiding' places. We could avoid them easily, of course, but it almost seems a disservice not to show them what a true ambush looks like...
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: La sutileza no parece ser el punto fuerte de quienes intentan emboscarnos, pues aguardan de forma muy visible a nuestra Caravana en lugares de “ocultamiento” bastante cuestionables. Claro que podríamos evitarlos con facilidad, pero casi parece una injusticia no mostrarles cómo se hace una emboscada de verdad...

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: A guide has tracked down our Caravan, offering to lead the way to our destination in exchange for a reasonable donation to his pockets. His price is frankly extortionate, but as they say in business, time is of the essence.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Un guía ha rastreado nuestra Caravana y se ofrece a conducirnos hasta nuestro destino a cambio de una generosa contribución a su bolsa. Su precio es francamente exorbitante, pero, como se suele decir en los negocios, el tiempo es oro.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: One of your caravans has crossed a Tomb King crypt, one owned by a dynasty that despises your caravans' objective. They demand all portions of your caravan's goods.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Una de tus caravanas ha entrado en la cripta de un Rey Funerario perteneciente a una dinastía que desprecia el objetivo de tus caravanas. Exigen todas las porciones de la mercancía de tu caravana.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: While traveling along the rolling dunes of Nehekhara our caravan chances upon a tomb that has been uncovered by the desert winds. The tomb appears to be untouched by time and ripe for the picking. Once inside, the men encounter a regally dressed skeleton who claims to be a prince and that our caravan leader is his long lost king. The skeleton promises to guard his “king” for eternity but all the men see are the riches that were buried here alongside the prince.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Mientras recorremos las dunas ondulantes de Nehekhara, nuestra caravana topa con una tumba que el viento del desierto ha dejado al descubierto. Parece inmaculada por el paso del tiempo y lista para ser saqueada. Una vez dentro, los hombres encuentran un esqueleto de porte regio que afirma ser un príncipe y que el líder de nuestra caravana es su rey perdido. El esqueleto promete proteger a su “rey” eternamente, pero los hombres solo ven las riquezas allí enterradas junto al príncipe.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: A cacophony of roars and feral shrieks rings out ahead of your Caravan – a Dark Elf Beastmaster approaches! By the look of his shackled beasts, he is recently returned from an expedition into Norsca and poses little threat, his retinue of hunters visibly weary and battered from their run-ins with the Northmen and critters of the tundra. With a tired Druchii sneer, he offers the Caravan one of his creatures in exchange for some slaves. Though we care little for the Dark Elf’s plight, such a beast could be useful against future threats.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Un estruendo de rugidos y chillidos salvajes resuena ante la Caravana: ¡un Amo de Bestias Elfo Oscuro se acerca! A juzgar por sus bestias encadenadas, regresa de una expedición a Norsca y no representa gran amenaza: su séquito de cazadores luce cansado y maltrecho tras los encontronazos con los norteños y las criaturas de la tundra. Con una sarcástica mueca druchii, ofrece a la Caravana una de sus criaturas a cambio de algunos esclavos. Nos importa poco el destino del Elfo Oscuro, pero podría servirnos esta bestia contra amenazas futuras.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: The day may have just begun, but one of the scouts has already spotted a wide, flat, stone platform in an isolated area. A series of eight steps leads to an eight-sided arena, with grooves carved in the floor to drain the blood spilled. Unmistakably, this is a Khornate combat shrine: the perfect location to tutor troops and beat the weakness out of them.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: El día apenas comienza, pero uno de los exploradores ya ha divisado una gran plataforma de piedra en una zona aislada. Una serie de ocho escalones conduce a una arena octogonal, con ranuras talladas en el suelo para drenar la sangre derramada. Sin duda, es un santuario de combate consagrado a Khorne: el lugar perfecto para adiestrar a las tropas y expulsarles la debilidad a golpes.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: As our caravan stops for the night at a shady oasis they encounter a tribe of the nomadic Strigany people. These folk ply the roads same as us but their customs are odd to say the least. The head of the tribe, a wise-woman bedecked in patchwork fabrics and fetishes of bone, meets with our caravan leader and offers to guide us to a shortcut through these dangerous lands in exchange for some of our cargo.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Mientras nuestra caravana se detiene para pasar la noche en un oasis sombrío, se topa con una tribu nómada de gente Strigany. Estos viajeros surcan los caminos igual que nosotros, aunque sus costumbres resultan, por decirlo suavemente, extrañas. La líder de la tribu, una mujer sabia cubierta con telas de retazos y fetiches de hueso, se reúne con el líder de nuestra caravana y ofrece guiarlo por un atajo a través de estas tierras peligrosas a cambio de parte de nuestra carga.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: A strong current is in front of our eyes. We can traverse this rough current and reach our destination sooner, but it may take the lives of some of our weaker personnel.
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Una fuerte corriente se yergue ante nuestros ojos. Podemos aventurarnos por estas bravas aguas y llegar antes a destino, pero quizá cueste la vida a parte de nuestro personal más débil.

dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_original: Your caravan stops some distance from a gigantic lamp-shaped tree. Is it merely a mirage? Surely a foreboding one, and right in the middle of the only viable path. What should we do?
dilemmas_localised_description_rhox_arab.value_translated: Nuestra caravana se detiene a cierta distancia de un gigantesco árbol en forma de lámpara. ¿Será solo un espejismo? Sin duda, un presagio inquietante, y justo en medio del único camino viable. ¿Qué debemos hacer?

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! Caravana del Maestro de Djinn

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! Ambushed by Rope Djinns!
Caravan Encounter! A Tithe of Bone
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! Un Diezmo de Hueso

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! A Dwarf Too Far
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! Un Enano Demasiado Lejos

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! The Mountain Folks Caravan
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! La Caravana del Pueblo de la Montaña
¡Encuentro de Caravana! Cuidado con las Marismas
¡Encuentro de Caravana! Campo de Batalla Fresco

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! One Man’s Treasure is Another Gnoblar’s Treasure
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! El Tesoro de uno es la Basura de un Gnoblar

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! Tribute to the Phoenix King
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! Tributo al Rey Fénix
¡Encuentro de Caravana! Artefacto de Magia Oscura

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! A Paramour in Pavona
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! Un amante en Pavona
¡Encuentro de Caravana! Cripta del Rey Funerario

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! Walk Like a Nehekharan
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! Camina como un Nehekharano
¡Encuentro de Caravana! El Amo de Bestias

dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_original: Caravan Encounter! The Heirs of Mourkain
Caravan Encounter! The Path of Storm
dilemmas_localised_title_rhox_araby_jaff.value_translated: ¡Encuentro de Caravana! El Camino de la Tormenta
¡Encuentro de Caravana! La Lámpara de Madera

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: Araby's coffers overflow with wealth, but we will never refuse a gift.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Las arcas de Arabia rebosan de riquezas, pero nunca rechazaremos un regalo.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: Power and wealth, what a man seeks, what a man needs.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Poder y riqueza, lo que un hombre busca, lo que un hombre necesita.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: May this gold bless our eternal alliance.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Que este oro bendiga nuestra eterna alianza.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: The Desert Spirits advise me otherwise, but I will accept your proposal.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Los Espíritus del Desierto me aconsejan lo contrario, pero aceptaré tu propuesta.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: You have my word, but not my confidence. Now go away!
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Tienes mi palabra, pero no mi confianza. ¡Ahora vete!

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: I hope the spirits don't punish me for this.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Espero que los espíritus no me castiguen por esto.
Mis Emires están de acuerdo con eso.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: May the Djinns be witnesses of our pact.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Que los Djinns sean testigos de nuestro pacto.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: Our alliance will be like an oasis between the sea of dunes.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Nuestra alianza será como un oasis entre el mar de dunas.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_original: Your gods smile at you, friend, the throne of Araby is with you.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Accep.value_translated: Tus dioses te sonríen, amigo, el trono de Arabia está contigo.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: I see that cunning lives inside you. Welcome you!
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Veo que la astucia vive dentro de ti. ¡Bienvenido!

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: I will have them prepare tialva and arag. We must celebrate!
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Haré que preparen tialva y arag. ¡Debemos celebrar!

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: Our future will be glorious. The world will tremble as we pass.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Nuestro futuro será glorioso. El mundo temblará cuando pasemos.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: Disappointment is what I feel, friend. I considered you wiser.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Decepción es lo que siento, amigo. Te consideraba más sabio.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: The weak cannot survive under the punishment of the desert.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Los débiles no pueden sobrevivir bajo el castigo del desierto.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: The Spirits are furious, you better leave my presence.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Los Espíritus están furiosos, será mejor que dejes mi presencia.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: If you have gods, you better start praying now.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Si tienes dioses, mejor empieza a rezar ahora.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: Your insolence is an insult. If you think you can reject me, fate will torment you.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Tu insolencia es una ofensa. Si piensas que puedes rechazarme, el destino te atormentará.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: You better leave, our scimitars are thirsty.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Será mejor que te vayas, nuestras cimitaras tienen sed.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: A distant power calls me, and soon the world will know its strength.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Un poder distante me llama, y pronto el mundo conocerá su fuerza.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: Against the powers that I will unleash, no one can oppose.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Contra los poderes que desataré, nadie podrá oponerse.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_original: I am Jaffar, remember that name, it will be the last thing your people will hear.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Ackno.value_translated: Soy Jaffar, recuerda ese nombre, será lo último que tu pueblo escuchará.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Cance.value_original: I think our presence here should not be prolonged.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Cance.value_translated: Creo que nuestra presencia aquí no debe prolongarse.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Cance.value_original: Dark days are approaching, because darker are the hearts of men.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Cance.value_translated: Días oscuros se aproximan, porque más oscuros son los corazones de los hombres.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Cance.value_original: What am I going to ally with weak vermin? Without your strength you are nothing
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Cance.value_translated: ¿Con quién voy a aliarme, con débiles roedores? Sin tu fuerza, no eres nada.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_original: By Kasoun's fiery sword, war call us!
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_translated: ¡Por la espada llameante de Kasoun, la guerra nos llama!

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_original: Wealth and glory await us, the whole world will be our kingdom.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_translated: Riqueza y gloria nos esperan, todo el mundo será nuestro reino.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_original: Come on friend, follow me to war, how much you want, there you will find it.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_translated: Vamos amigo, sígueme a la guerra, lo que desees, allí lo encontrarás.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_original: You can't imagine the riches of Araby, how do you intend to possess them?
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_translated: No puedes imaginarte las riquezas de Arabia, ¿cómo pretendes poseerlas?

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_original: The tribute is necessary for those who can only serve.
diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_translated: El tributo es necesario para aquellos que solo pueden servir.

diplomacy_strings_string_Araby_Dip_Deman.value_original: An insignificant payment, but if you settle for this, good for you.
